  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 51ee3e37f5ded7941ab6216610f6fc67, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: Introduction
      content: '  Many people have set out to write accounts about the events that
        have been fulfilled among us. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They used the eyewitness reports circulating among us from the early
        disciples.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:2 '
        content: Greek <b>from those who from the beginning were servants of the
          word.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Having carefully investigated everything from the beginning, I also
        have decided to write an accurate account for you, most honorable Theophilus, '
      comments: []
    - title: The Birth of John the Baptist Foretold
      content: 'so you can be certain of the truth of everything you were taught.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When Herod was king of Judea, there was a Jewish priest named Zechariah.
        He was a member of the priestly order of Abijah, and his wife, Elizabeth,
        was also from the priestly line of Aaron. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Zechariah and Elizabeth were righteous in God\u2019s eyes, careful
        to obey all of the Lord\u2019s commandments and regulations. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They had no children because Elizabeth was unable to conceive, and
        they were both very old.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'One day Zechariah was serving God in the Temple, for his order was
        on duty that week. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As was the custom of the priests, he was chosen by lot to enter the
        sanctuary of the Lord and burn incense. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'While the incense was being burned, a great crowd stood outside,
        praying.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'While Zechariah was in the sanctuary, an angel of the Lord appeared
        to him, standing to the right of the incense altar. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Zechariah was shaken and overwhelmed with fear when he saw him. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But the angel said, \u201CDon\u2019t be afraid, Zechariah! God has
        heard your prayer. Your wife, Elizabeth, will give you a son, and you are
        to name him John. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will have great joy and gladness, and many will rejoice at his
        birth, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'for he will be great in the eyes of the Lord. He must never touch
        wine or other alcoholic drinks. He will be filled with the Holy Spirit, even
        before his birth.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:15 '
        content: Or <b>even from birth.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'And he will turn many Israelites to the Lord their God. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He will be a man with the spirit and power of Elijah. He will prepare
        the people for the coming of the Lord. He will turn the hearts of the fathers
        to their children,[[COMMENT(0)]] and he will cause those who are rebellious
        to accept the wisdom of the godly.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:17 '
        content: See Mal 4:5-6.
    - title: 
      content: "Zechariah said to the angel, \u201CHow can I be sure this will happen?
        I\u2019m an old man now, and my wife is also well along in years.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the angel said, \u201CI am Gabriel! I stand in the very presence
        of God. It was he who sent me to bring you this good news! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But now, since you didn\u2019t believe what I said, you will be silent
        and unable to speak until the child is born. For my words will certainly
        be fulfilled at the proper time.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Meanwhile, the people were waiting for Zechariah to come out of the
        sanctuary, wondering why he was taking so long. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When he finally did come out, he couldn\u2019t speak to them. Then
        they realized from his gestures and his silence that he must have seen a
        vision in the sanctuary.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When Zechariah\u2019s week of service in the Temple was over, he
        returned home. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Soon afterward his wife, Elizabeth, became pregnant and went into
        seclusion for five months. '
      comments: []
    - title: The Birth of Jesus Foretold
      content: "\u201CHow kind the Lord is!\u201D she exclaimed. \u201CHe has taken
        away my disgrace of having no children.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In the sixth month of Elizabeth\u2019s pregnancy, God sent the angel
        Gabriel to Nazareth, a village in Galilee, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'to a virgin named Mary. She was engaged to be married to a man named
        Joseph, a descendant of King David. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Gabriel appeared to her and said, \u201CGreetings,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        favored woman! The Lord is with you![[COMMENT(1)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:28a '
        content: Or <b>Rejoice.</b>
      - number: '1:28b '
        content: Some manuscripts add <b>Blessed are you among women.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Confused and disturbed, Mary tried to think what the angel could
        mean. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CDon\u2019t be afraid, Mary,\u201D the angel told her, \u201Cfor
        you have found favor with God! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will conceive and give birth to a son, and you will name him
        Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He will be very great and will be called the Son of the Most High.
        The Lord God will give him the throne of his ancestor David. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And he will reign over Israel[[COMMENT(0)]] forever; his Kingdom
        will never end!\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:33 '
        content: Greek <b>over the house of Jacob.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Mary asked the angel, \u201CBut how can this happen? I am a virgin.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The angel replied, \u201CThe Holy Spirit will come upon you, and
        the power of the Most High will overshadow you. So the baby to be born will
        be holy, and he will be called the Son of God. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "What\u2019s more, your relative Elizabeth has become pregnant in
        her old age! People used to say she was barren, but she has conceived a son
        and is now in her sixth month. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the word of God will never fail.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:37 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>For nothing is impossible with God.</b>
    - title: Mary Visits Elizabeth
      content: "Mary responded, \u201CI am the Lord\u2019s servant. May everything
        you have said about me come true.\u201D And then the angel left her.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A few days later Mary hurried to the hill country of Judea, to the
        town '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'where Zechariah lived. She entered the house and greeted Elizabeth. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "At the sound of Mary\u2019s greeting, Elizabeth\u2019s child leaped
        within her, and Elizabeth was filled with the Holy Spirit.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Elizabeth gave a glad cry and exclaimed to Mary, \u201CGod has blessed
        you above all women, and your child is blessed. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Why am I so honored, that the mother of my Lord should visit me? '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When I heard your greeting, the baby in my womb jumped for joy. '
      comments: []
    - title: "The Magnificat: Mary\u2019s Song of Praise"
      content: "You are blessed because you believed that the Lord would do what
        he said.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Mary responded,\u201COh, how my soul praises the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'How my spirit rejoices in God my Savior!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For he took notice of his lowly servant girl,and from now on all
        generations will call me blessed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the Mighty One is holy,and he has done great things for me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He shows mercy from generation to generationto all who fear him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'His mighty arm has done tremendous things!He has scattered the proud
        and haughty ones.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He has brought down princes from their thronesand exalted the humble.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He has filled the hungry with good thingsand sent the rich away with
        empty hands.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He has helped his servant Israeland remembered to be merciful.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For he made this promise to our ancestors,to Abraham and his children
        forever.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: The Birth of John the Baptist
      content: 'Mary stayed with Elizabeth about three months and then went back
        to her own home.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When it was time for Elizabeth\u2019s baby to be born, she gave birth
        to a son. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And when her neighbors and relatives heard that the Lord had been
        very merciful to her, everyone rejoiced with her.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When the baby was eight days old, they all came for the circumcision
        ceremony. They wanted to name him Zechariah, after his father. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But Elizabeth said, \u201CNo! His name is John!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhat?\u201D they exclaimed. \u201CThere is no one in all your
        family by that name.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So they used gestures to ask the baby\u2019s father what he wanted
        to name him. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He motioned for a writing tablet, and to everyone\u2019s surprise
        he wrote, \u201CHis name is John.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Instantly Zechariah could speak again, and he began praising God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Awe fell upon the whole neighborhood, and the news of what had happened
        spread throughout the Judean hills. '
      comments: []
    - title: "Zechariah\u2019s Prophecy"
      content: "Everyone who heard about it reflected on these events and asked,
        \u201CWhat will this child turn out to be?\u201D For the hand of the Lord
        was surely upon him in a special way.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then his father, Zechariah, was filled with the Holy Spirit and gave
        this prophecy:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CPraise the Lord, the God of Israel,because he has visited and
        redeemed his people.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He has sent us a mighty Savior[[COMMENT(0)]]from the royal line of
        his servant David,  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:69 '
        content: Greek <b>has raised up a horn of salvation for us.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'just as he promisedthrough his holy prophets long ago.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Now we will be saved from our enemiesand from all who hate us.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He has been merciful to our ancestorsby remembering his sacred covenant\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'the covenant he swore with an oathto our ancestor Abraham.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We have been rescued from our enemiesso we can serve God without
        fear,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'in holiness and righteousnessfor as long as we live.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAnd you, my little son,will be called the prophet of the Most
        High,because you will prepare the way for the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You will tell his people how to find salvationthrough forgiveness
        of their sins.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Because of God\u2019s tender mercy,the morning light from heaven
        is about to break upon us,[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:78 '
        content: Or <b>the Morning Light from Heaven is about to visit us.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "to give light to those who sit in darkness and in the shadow of death,and
        to guide us to the path of peace.\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Birth of Jesus
      content: '  At that time the Roman emperor, Augustus, decreed that a census
        should be taken throughout the Roman Empire. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: '(This was the first census taken when Quirinius was governor of Syria.) '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'All returned to their own ancestral towns to register for this census. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And because Joseph was a descendant of King David, he had to go to
        Bethlehem in Judea, David\u2019s ancient home. He traveled there from the
        village of Nazareth in Galilee. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He took with him Mary, to whom he was engaged, who was now expecting
        a child.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And while they were there, the time came for her baby to be born. '
      comments: []
    - title: The Shepherds and Angels
      content: 'She gave birth to her firstborn son. She wrapped him snugly in strips
        of cloth and laid him in a manger, because there was no lodging available
        for them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'That night there were shepherds staying in the fields nearby, guarding
        their flocks of sheep. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Suddenly, an angel of the Lord appeared among them, and the radiance
        of the Lord\u2019s glory surrounded them. They were terrified, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "but the angel reassured them. \u201CDon\u2019t be afraid!\u201D he
        said. \u201CI bring you good news that will bring great joy to all people. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The Savior\u2014yes, the Messiah, the Lord\u2014has been born today
        in Bethlehem, the city of David! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And you will recognize him by this sign: You will find a baby wrapped
        snugly in strips of cloth, lying in a manger.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Suddenly, the angel was joined by a vast host of others\u2014the
        armies of heaven\u2014praising God and saying,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGlory to God in highest heaven,and peace on earth to those
        with whom God is pleased.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When the angels had returned to heaven, the shepherds said to each
        other, \u201CLet\u2019s go to Bethlehem! Let\u2019s see this thing that has
        happened, which the Lord has told us about.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They hurried to the village and found Mary and Joseph. And there
        was the baby, lying in the manger. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'After seeing him, the shepherds told everyone what had happened and
        what the angel had said to them about this child. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All who heard the shepherds\u2019 story were astonished, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'but Mary kept all these things in her heart and thought about them
        often. '
      comments: []
    - title: Jesus Is Presented in the Temple
      content: 'The shepherds went back to their flocks, glorifying and praising
        God for all they had heard and seen. It was just as the angel had told them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Eight days later, when the baby was circumcised, he was named Jesus,
        the name given him by the angel even before he was conceived.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then it was time for their purification offering, as required by
        the law of Moses after the birth of a child; so his parents took him to Jerusalem
        to present him to the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The law of the Lord says, \u201CIf a woman\u2019s first child is
        a boy, he must be dedicated to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:23 '
        content: Exod 13:2.
    - title: The Prophecy of Simeon
      content: "So they offered the sacrifice required in the law of the Lord\u2014\u201Ceither
        a pair of turtledoves or two young pigeons.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:24 '
        content: Lev 12:8.
    - title: 
      content: 'At that time there was a man in Jerusalem named Simeon. He was righteous
        and devout and was eagerly waiting for the Messiah to come and rescue Israel.
        The Holy Spirit was upon him '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "and had revealed to him that he would not die until he had seen the
        Lord\u2019s Messiah. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'That day the Spirit led him to the Temple. So when Mary and Joseph
        came to present the baby Jesus to the Lord as the law required, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Simeon was there. He took the child in his arms and praised God,
        saying,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CSovereign Lord, now let your servant die in peace,as you have
        promised.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I have seen your salvation,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'which you have prepared for all people.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He is a light to reveal God to the nations,and he is the glory of
        your people Israel!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Jesus\u2019 parents were amazed at what was being said about him. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Simeon blessed them, and he said to Mary, the baby\u2019s mother,
        \u201CThis child is destined to cause many in Israel to fall, and many others
        to rise. He has been sent as a sign from God, but many will oppose him. "
      comments: []
    - title: The Prophecy of Anna
      content: "As a result, the deepest thoughts of many hearts will be revealed.
        And a sword will pierce your very soul.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Anna, a prophet, was also there in the Temple. She was the daughter
        of Phanuel from the tribe of Asher, and she was very old. Her husband died
        when they had been married only seven years. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then she lived as a widow to the age of eighty-four.[[COMMENT(0)]]
        She never left the Temple but stayed there day and night, worshiping God
        with fasting and prayer. '
      comments:
      - number: '2:37 '
        content: Or <b>She had been a widow for eighty-four years.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'She came along just as Simeon was talking with Mary and Joseph, and
        she began praising God. She talked about the child to everyone who had been
        waiting expectantly for God to rescue Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When Jesus\u2019 parents had fulfilled all the requirements of the
        law of the Lord, they returned home to Nazareth in Galilee. "
      comments: []
    - title: Jesus Speaks with the Teachers
      content: "There the child grew up healthy and strong. He was filled with wisdom,
        and God\u2019s favor was on him.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Every year Jesus\u2019 parents went to Jerusalem for the Passover
        festival. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When Jesus was twelve years old, they attended the festival as usual. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "After the celebration was over, they started home to Nazareth, but
        Jesus stayed behind in Jerusalem. His parents didn\u2019t miss him at first, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "because they assumed he was among the other travelers. But when he
        didn\u2019t show up that evening, they started looking for him among their
        relatives and friends.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When they couldn\u2019t find him, they went back to Jerusalem to
        search for him there. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Three days later they finally discovered him in the Temple, sitting
        among the religious teachers, listening to them and asking questions. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'All who heard him were amazed at his understanding and his answers.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "His parents didn\u2019t know what to think. \u201CSon,\u201D his
        mother said to him, \u201Cwhy have you done this to us? Your father and I
        have been frantic, searching for you everywhere.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CBut why did you need to search?\u201D he asked. \u201CDidn\u2019t
        you know that I must be in my Father\u2019s house?\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:49 '
        content: "Or <b>\u201CDidn\u2019t you realize that I should be involved with
          my Father\u2019s affairs?\u201D</b>"
    - title: 
      content: "But they didn\u2019t understand what he meant.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then he returned to Nazareth with them and was obedient to them.
        And his mother stored all these things in her heart.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: John the Baptist Prepares the Way
      content: '  It was now the fifteenth year of the reign of Tiberius, the Roman
        emperor. Pontius Pilate was governor over Judea; Herod Antipas was ruler[[COMMENT(0)]]
        over Galilee; his brother Philip was ruler[[COMMENT(1)]] over Iturea and
        Traconitis; Lysanias was ruler over Abilene. '
      comments:
      - number: '3:1a '
        content: Greek <b>Herod was tetrarch. </b>Herod Antipas was a son of King
          Herod.
      - number: '3:1b '
        content: Greek <b>tetrarch; </b>also in 3:1c.
    - title: 
      content: 'Annas and Caiaphas were the high priests. At this time a message
        from God came to John son of Zechariah, who was living in the wilderness. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then John went from place to place on both sides of the Jordan River,
        preaching that people should be baptized to show that they had repented of
        their sins and turned to God to be forgiven. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Isaiah had spoken of John when he said,\u201CHe is a voice shouting
        in the wilderness,\u2018Prepare the way for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        coming!Clear the road for him!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The valleys will be filled,and the mountains and hills made level.The
        curves will be straightened,and the rough places made smooth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And then all people will seethe salvation sent from God.\u2019\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:4-6 '
        content: Isa 40:3-5 (Greek version).
    - title: 
      content: "When the crowds came to John for baptism, he said, \u201CYou brood
        of snakes! Who warned you to flee the coming wrath? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Prove by the way you live that you have repented of your sins and
        turned to God. Don\u2019t just say to each other, \u2018We\u2019re safe,
        for we are descendants of Abraham.\u2019 That means nothing, for I tell you,
        God can create children of Abraham from these very stones. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Even now the ax of God\u2019s judgment is poised, ready to sever
        the roots of the trees. Yes, every tree that does not produce good fruit
        will be chopped down and thrown into the fire.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The crowds asked, \u201CWhat should we do?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "John replied, \u201CIf you have two shirts, give one to the poor.
        If you have food, share it with those who are hungry.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Even corrupt tax collectors came to be baptized and asked, \u201CTeacher,
        what should we do?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He replied, \u201CCollect no more taxes than the government requires.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhat should we do?\u201D asked some soldiers.John replied,
        \u201CDon\u2019t extort money or make false accusations. And be content with
        your pay.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Everyone was expecting the Messiah to come soon, and they were eager
        to know whether John might be the Messiah. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "John answered their questions by saying, \u201CI baptize you with[[COMMENT(0)]]
        water; but someone is coming soon who is greater than I am\u2014so much greater
        that I\u2019m not even worthy to be his slave and untie the straps of his
        sandals. He will baptize you with the Holy Spirit and with fire.[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:16a '
        content: Or <b>in.</b>
      - number: '3:16b '
        content: Or <b>in the Holy Spirit and in fire.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "He is ready to separate the chaff from the wheat with his winnowing
        fork. Then he will clean up the threshing area, gathering the wheat into
        his barn but burning the chaff with never-ending fire.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'John used many such warnings as he announced the Good News to the
        people.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "John also publicly criticized Herod Antipas, the ruler of Galilee,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        for marrying Herodias, his brother\u2019s wife, and for many other wrongs
        he had done. "
      comments:
      - number: '3:19 '
        content: Greek <b>Herod the tetrarch.</b>
    - title: The Baptism of Jesus
      content: 'So Herod put John in prison, adding this sin to his many others.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'One day when the crowds were being baptized, Jesus himself was baptized.
        As he was praying, the heavens opened, '
      comments: []
    - title: The Ancestors of Jesus
      content: "and the Holy Spirit, in bodily form, descended on him like a dove.
        And a voice from heaven said, \u201CYou are my dearly loved Son, and you
        bring me great joy.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:22 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>my Son, and today I have become your Father.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Jesus was about thirty years old when he began his public ministry.Jesus
        was known as the son of Joseph.Joseph was the son of Heli.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Heli was the son of Matthat.Matthat was the son of Levi.Levi was
        the son of Melki.Melki was the son of Jannai.Jannai was the son of Joseph.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Joseph was the son of Mattathias.Mattathias was the son of Amos.Amos
        was the son of Nahum.Nahum was the son of Esli.Esli was the son of Naggai.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Naggai was the son of Maath.Maath was the son of Mattathias.Mattathias
        was the son of Semein.Semein was the son of Josech.Josech was the son of
        Joda.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Joda was the son of Joanan.Joanan was the son of Rhesa.Rhesa was
        the son of Zerubbabel.Zerubbabel was the son of Shealtiel.Shealtiel was the
        son of Neri.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Neri was the son of Melki.Melki was the son of Addi.Addi was the
        son of Cosam.Cosam was the son of Elmadam.Elmadam was the son of Er.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Er was the son of Joshua.Joshua was the son of Eliezer.Eliezer was
        the son of Jorim.Jorim was the son of Matthat.Matthat was the son of Levi.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Levi was the son of Simeon.Simeon was the son of Judah.Judah was
        the son of Joseph.Joseph was the son of Jonam.Jonam was the son of Eliakim.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Eliakim was the son of Melea.Melea was the son of Menna.Menna was
        the son of Mattatha.Mattatha was the son of Nathan.Nathan was the son of
        David.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'David was the son of Jesse.Jesse was the son of Obed.Obed was the
        son of Boaz.Boaz was the son of Salmon.[[COMMENT(0)]]Salmon was the son of
        Nahshon.  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:32 '
        content: Greek <b>Sala, </b>a variant spelling of Salmon; also in 3:32b.
          See Ruth 4:20-21.
    - title: 
      content: 'Nahshon was the son of Amminadab.Amminadab was the son of Admin.Admin
        was the son of Arni.[[COMMENT(0)]]Arni was the son of Hezron.Hezron was the
        son of Perez.Perez was the son of Judah.  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:33 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>Amminadab was the son of Aram. </b><b>Arni
          </b>and <b>Aram </b>are alternate spellings of Ram. See 1 Chr 2:9-10.
    - title: 
      content: 'Judah was the son of Jacob.Jacob was the son of Isaac.Isaac was the
        son of Abraham.Abraham was the son of Terah.Terah was the son of Nahor.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Nahor was the son of Serug.Serug was the son of Reu.Reu was the son
        of Peleg.Peleg was the son of Eber.Eber was the son of Shelah.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Shelah was the son of Cainan.Cainan was the son of Arphaxad.Arphaxad
        was the son of Shem.Shem was the son of Noah.Noah was the son of Lamech.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Lamech was the son of Methuselah.Methuselah was the son of Enoch.Enoch
        was the son of Jared.Jared was the son of Mahalalel.Mahalalel was the son
        of Kenan.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Temptation of Jesus
      content: '  Then Jesus, full of the Holy Spirit, returned from the Jordan River.
        He was led by the Spirit in the wilderness,[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:1 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>into the wilderness.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'where he was tempted by the devil for forty days. Jesus ate nothing
        all that time and became very hungry.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the devil said to him, \u201CIf you are the Son of God, tell
        this stone to become a loaf of bread.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But Jesus told him, \u201CNo! The Scriptures say, \u2018People do
        not live by bread alone.\u2019[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:4 '
        content: 'Deut 8:3.  '
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the devil took him up and revealed to him all the kingdoms of
        the world in a moment of time. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI will give you the glory of these kingdoms and authority over
        them,\u201D the devil said, \u201Cbecause they are mine to give to anyone
        I please. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will give it all to you if you will worship me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Jesus replied, \u201CThe Scriptures say,  \u2018You must worship
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God  and serve only him.\u2019  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        \u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:8 '
        content: '  Deut 6:13.  '
    - title: 
      content: "Then the devil took him to Jerusalem, to the highest point of the
        Temple, and said, \u201CIf you are the Son of God, jump off! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the Scriptures say,\u2018He will order his angels to protect
        and guard you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And they will hold you up with their handsso you won\u2019t even
        hurt your foot on a stone.\u2019[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:10-11 '
        content: Ps 91:11-12.
    - title: 
      content: "Jesus responded, \u201CThe Scriptures also say, \u2018You must not
        test the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God.\u2019[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:12 '
        content: 'Deut 6:16.  '
    - title: Jesus Rejected at Nazareth
      content: 'When the devil had finished tempting Jesus, he left him until the
        next opportunity came.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Jesus returned to Galilee, filled with the Holy Spirit\u2019s
        power. Reports about him spread quickly through the whole region. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He taught regularly in their synagogues and was praised by everyone.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When he came to the village of Nazareth, his boyhood home, he went
        as usual to the synagogue on the Sabbath and stood up to read the Scriptures. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The scroll of Isaiah the prophet was handed to him. He unrolled the
        scroll and found the place where this was written:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CThe Spirit of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is upon me, 
        for he has anointed me to bring Good News to the poor.  He has sent me to
        proclaim that captives will be released,  that the blind will see,  that
        the oppressed will be set free,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  and that the time of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s favor
        has come.  [[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps>  </smallcaps>  \u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:18-19 '
        content: '  Or   <b>and to proclaim the acceptable year of the <span class="ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf">Lord</span>.
          </b>Isa 61:1-2 (Greek version); 58:6.  '
    - title: 
      content: 'He rolled up the scroll, handed it back to the attendant, and sat
        down. All eyes in the synagogue looked at him intently. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then he began to speak to them. \u201CThe Scripture you\u2019ve just
        heard has been fulfilled this very day!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Everyone spoke well of him and was amazed by the gracious words that
        came from his lips. \u201CHow can this be?\u201D they asked. \u201CIsn\u2019t
        this Joseph\u2019s son?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then he said, \u201CYou will undoubtedly quote me this proverb: \u2018Physician,
        heal yourself\u2019\u2014meaning, \u2018Do miracles here in your hometown
        like those you did in Capernaum.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But I tell you the truth, no prophet is accepted in his own hometown.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CCertainly there were many needy widows in Israel in Elijah\u2019s
        time, when the heavens were closed for three and a half years, and a severe
        famine devastated the land.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yet Elijah was not sent to any of them. He was sent instead to a
        foreigner\u2014a widow of Zarephath in the land of Sidon.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And many in Israel had leprosy in the time of the prophet Elisha,
        but the only one healed was Naaman, a Syrian.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When they heard this, the people in the synagogue were furious. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Jumping up, they mobbed him and forced him to the edge of the hill
        on which the town was built. They intended to push him over the cliff, '
      comments: []
    - title: Jesus Casts Out a Demon
      content: 'but he passed right through the crowd and went on his way.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then Jesus went to Capernaum, a town in Galilee, and taught there
        in the synagogue every Sabbath day. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'There, too, the people were amazed at his teaching, for he spoke
        with authority.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Once when he was in the synagogue, a man possessed by a demon\u2014an
        evil[[COMMENT(0)]] spirit\u2014cried out, shouting, "
      comments:
      - number: '4:33 '
        content: Greek <b>unclean; </b>also in 4:36.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGo away! Why are you interfering with us, Jesus of Nazareth?
        Have you come to destroy us? I know who you are\u2014the Holy One of God!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But Jesus reprimanded him. \u201CBe quiet! Come out of the man,\u201D
        he ordered. At that, the demon threw the man to the floor as the crowd watched;
        then it came out of him without hurting him further.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Amazed, the people exclaimed, \u201CWhat authority and power this
        man\u2019s words possess! Even evil spirits obey him, and they flee at his
        command!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: Jesus Heals Many People
      content: 'The news about Jesus spread through every village in the entire region.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "After leaving the synagogue that day, Jesus went to Simon\u2019s
        home, where he found Simon\u2019s mother-in-law very sick with a high fever.
        \u201CPlease heal her,\u201D everyone begged. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Standing at her bedside, he rebuked the fever, and it left her. And
        she got up at once and prepared a meal for them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As the sun went down that evening, people throughout the village
        brought sick family members to Jesus. No matter what their diseases were,
        the touch of his hand healed every one. '
      comments: []
    - title: Jesus Continues to Preach
      content: "Many were possessed by demons; and the demons came out at his command,
        shouting, \u201CYou are the Son of God!\u201D But because they knew he was
        the Messiah, he rebuked them and refused to let them speak.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Early the next morning Jesus went out to an isolated place. The crowds
        searched everywhere for him, and when they finally found him, they begged
        him not to leave them. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But he replied, \u201CI must preach the Good News of the Kingdom
        of God in other towns, too, because that is why I was sent.\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The First Disciples
      content: '  One day as Jesus was preaching on the shore of the Sea of Galilee,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        great crowds pressed in on him to listen to the word of God. '
      comments:
      - number: '5:1 '
        content: Greek <b>Lake Gennesaret, </b>another name for the Sea of Galilee.
    - title: 
      content: "He noticed two empty boats at the water\u2019s edge, for the fishermen
        had left them and were washing their nets. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Stepping into one of the boats, Jesus asked Simon,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        its owner, to push it out into the water. So he sat in the boat and taught
        the crowds from there.  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:3 '
        content: "<b>Simon </b>is called \u201CPeter\u201D in 6:14 and thereafter."
    - title: 
      content: "When he had finished speaking, he said to Simon, \u201CNow go out
        where it is deeper, and let down your nets to catch some fish.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CMaster,\u201D Simon replied, \u201Cwe worked hard all last
        night and didn\u2019t catch a thing. But if you say so, I\u2019ll let the
        nets down again.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And this time their nets were so full of fish they began to tear! '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A shout for help brought their partners in the other boat, and soon
        both boats were filled with fish and on the verge of sinking.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When Simon Peter realized what had happened, he fell to his knees
        before Jesus and said, \u201COh, Lord, please leave me\u2014I\u2019m such
        a sinful man.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For he was awestruck by the number of fish they had caught, as were
        the others with him. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "His partners, James and John, the sons of Zebedee, were also amazed.Jesus
        replied to Simon, \u201CDon\u2019t be afraid! From now on you\u2019ll be
        fishing for people!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Jesus Heals a Man with Leprosy
      content: 'And as soon as they landed, they left everything and followed Jesus.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "In one of the villages, Jesus met a man with an advanced case of
        leprosy. When the man saw Jesus, he bowed with his face to the ground, begging
        to be healed. \u201CLord,\u201D he said, \u201Cif you are willing, you can
        heal me and make me clean.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Jesus reached out and touched him. \u201CI am willing,\u201D he said.
        \u201CBe healed!\u201D And instantly the leprosy disappeared. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Jesus instructed him not to tell anyone what had happened. He
        said, \u201CGo to the priest and let him examine you. Take along the offering
        required in the law of Moses for those who have been healed of leprosy.[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        This will be a public testimony that you have been cleansed.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:14 '
        content: See Lev 14:2-32.
    - title: 
      content: "But despite Jesus\u2019 instructions, the report of his power spread
        even faster, and vast crowds came to hear him preach and to be healed of
        their diseases. "
      comments: []
    - title: Jesus Heals a Paralyzed Man
      content: 'But Jesus often withdrew to the wilderness for prayer.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "One day while Jesus was teaching, some Pharisees and teachers of
        religious law were sitting nearby. (It seemed that these men showed up from
        every village in all Galilee and Judea, as well as from Jerusalem.) And the
        Lord\u2019s healing power was strongly with Jesus.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Some men came carrying a paralyzed man on a sleeping mat. They tried
        to take him inside to Jesus, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "but they couldn\u2019t reach him because of the crowd. So they went
        up to the roof and took off some tiles. Then they lowered the sick man on
        his mat down into the crowd, right in front of Jesus. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Seeing their faith, Jesus said to the man, \u201CYoung man, your
        sins are forgiven.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But the Pharisees and teachers of religious law said to themselves,
        \u201CWho does he think he is? That\u2019s blasphemy! Only God can forgive
        sins!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Jesus knew what they were thinking, so he asked them, \u201CWhy do
        you question this in your hearts?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Is it easier to say \u2018Your sins are forgiven,\u2019 or \u2018Stand
        up and walk\u2019?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So I will prove to you that the Son of Man[[COMMENT(0)]]  has the
        authority on earth to forgive sins.\u201D Then Jesus turned to the paralyzed
        man and said, \u201CStand up, pick up your mat, and go home!\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:24 '
        content: "\u201CSon of Man\u201D is a title Jesus used for himself."
    - title: 
      content: 'And immediately, as everyone watched, the man jumped up, picked up
        his mat, and went home praising God. '
      comments: []
    - title: Jesus Calls Levi (Matthew)
      content: "Everyone was gripped with great wonder and awe, and they praised
        God, exclaiming, \u201CWe have seen amazing things today!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Later, as Jesus left the town, he saw a tax collector named Levi
        sitting at his tax collector\u2019s booth. \u201CFollow me and be my disciple,\u201D
        Jesus said to him. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So Levi got up, left everything, and followed him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Later, Levi held a banquet in his home with Jesus as the guest of
        honor. Many of Levi\u2019s fellow tax collectors and other guests also ate
        with them. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But the Pharisees and their teachers of religious law complained
        bitterly to Jesus\u2019 disciples, \u201CWhy do you eat and drink with such
        scum?[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:30 '
        content: Greek <b>with tax collectors and sinners?</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Jesus answered them, \u201CHealthy people don\u2019t need a doctor\u2014sick
        people do.  "
      comments: []
    - title: A Discussion about Fasting
      content: "I have come to call not those who think they are righteous, but those
        who know they are sinners and need to repent.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "One day some people said to Jesus, \u201CJohn the Baptist\u2019s
        disciples fast and pray regularly, and so do the disciples of the Pharisees.
        Why are your disciples always eating and drinking?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Jesus responded, \u201CDo wedding guests fast while celebrating with
        the groom? Of course not.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But someday the groom will be taken away from them, and then they
        will fast.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Jesus gave them this illustration: \u201CNo one tears a piece
        of cloth from a new garment and uses it to patch an old garment. For then
        the new garment would be ruined, and the new patch wouldn\u2019t even match
        the old garment.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CAnd no one puts new wine into old wineskins. For the new
        wine would burst the wineskins, spilling the wine and ruining the skins.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'New wine must be stored in new wineskins.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Discussion about the Sabbath
      content: '  One Sabbath day as Jesus was walking through some grainfields,
        his disciples broke off heads of grain, rubbed off the husks in their hands,
        and ate the grain. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But some Pharisees said, \u201CWhy are you breaking the law by harvesting
        grain on the Sabbath?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Jesus replied, \u201CHaven\u2019t you read in the Scriptures what
        David did when he and his companions were hungry?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He went into the house of God and broke the law by eating the sacred
        loaves of bread that only the priests can eat. He also gave some to his companions.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Jesus Heals on the Sabbath
      content: "And Jesus added, \u201CThe Son of Man[[COMMENT(0)]]  is Lord, even
        over the Sabbath.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:5 '
        content: "\u201CSon of Man\u201D is a title Jesus used for himself."
    - title: 
      content: 'On another Sabbath day, a man with a deformed right hand was in the
        synagogue while Jesus was teaching. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The teachers of religious law and the Pharisees watched Jesus closely.
        If he healed the man\u2019s hand, they planned to accuse him of working on
        the Sabbath.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But Jesus knew their thoughts. He said to the man with the deformed
        hand, \u201CCome and stand in front of everyone.\u201D So the man came forward. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Jesus said to his critics, \u201CI have a question for you.
        Does the law permit good deeds on the Sabbath, or is it a day for doing evil?
        Is this a day to save life or to destroy it?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He looked around at them one by one and then said to the man, \u201CHold
        out your hand.\u201D So the man held out his hand, and it was restored! "
      comments: []
    - title: Jesus Chooses the Twelve Apostles
      content: 'At this, the enemies of Jesus were wild with rage and began to discuss
        what to do with him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'One day soon afterward Jesus went up on a mountain to pray, and he
        prayed to God all night. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'At daybreak he called together all of his disciples and chose twelve
        of them to be apostles. Here are their names:  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Simon (whom he named Peter),Andrew (Peter\u2019s brother),James,John,Philip,Bartholomew,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Matthew,Thomas,James (son of Alphaeus),Simon (who was called the
        zealot),  '
      comments: []
    - title: Crowds Follow Jesus
      content: 'Judas (son of James),Judas Iscariot (who later betrayed him).  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When they came down from the mountain, the disciples stood with Jesus
        on a large, level area, surrounded by many of his followers and by the crowds.
        There were people from all over Judea and from Jerusalem and from as far
        north as the seacoasts of Tyre and Sidon. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They had come to hear him and to be healed of their diseases; and
        those troubled by evil[[COMMENT(0)]] spirits were healed. '
      comments:
      - number: '6:18 '
        content: Greek <b>unclean.</b>
    - title: The Beatitudes
      content: 'Everyone tried to touch him, because healing power went out from
        him, and he healed everyone.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Jesus turned to his disciples and said,  \u201CGod blesses you
        who are poor,  for the Kingdom of God is yours.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: '  God blesses you who are hungry now,  for you will be satisfied. 
        God blesses you who weep now,  for in due time you will laugh.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: '  What blessings await you when people hate you and exclude you and
        mock you and curse you as evil because you follow the Son of Man.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Sorrows Foretold
      content: 'When that happens, be happy! Yes, leap for joy! For a great reward
        awaits you in heaven. And remember, their ancestors treated the ancient prophets
        that same way.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CWhat sorrow awaits you who are rich,  for you have your only
        happiness now.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: '  What sorrow awaits you who are fat and prosperous now,  for a time
        of awful hunger awaits you.  What sorrow awaits you who laugh now,  for your
        laughing will turn to mourning and sorrow.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Love for Enemies
      content: '  What sorrow awaits you who are praised by the crowds,  for their
        ancestors also praised false prophets.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CBut to you who are willing to listen, I say, love your enemies!
        Do good to those who hate you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Bless those who curse you. Pray for those who hurt you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If someone slaps you on one cheek, offer the other cheek also. If
        someone demands your coat, offer your shirt also.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Give to anyone who asks; and when things are taken away from you,
        don\u2019t try to get them back.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do to others as you would like them to do to you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CIf you love only those who love you, why should you get credit
        for that? Even sinners love those who love them!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And if you do good only to those who do good to you, why should you
        get credit? Even sinners do that much!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And if you lend money only to those who can repay you, why should
        you get credit? Even sinners will lend to other sinners for a full return.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CLove your enemies! Do good to them. Lend to them without
        expecting to be repaid. Then your reward from heaven will be very great,
        and you will truly be acting as children of the Most High, for he is kind
        to those who are unthankful and wicked.  "
      comments: []
    - title: Do Not Judge Others
      content: 'You must be compassionate, just as your Father is compassionate.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CDo not judge others, and you will not be judged. Do not condemn
        others, or it will all come back against you. Forgive others, and you will
        be forgiven.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Give, and you will receive. Your gift will return to you in full\u2014pressed
        down, shaken together to make room for more, running over, and poured into
        your lap. The amount you give will determine the amount you get back.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:38 '
        content: Or <b>The measure you give will be the measure you get back.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Then Jesus gave the following illustration: \u201CCan one blind person
        lead another? Won\u2019t they both fall into a ditch?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Students[[COMMENT(0)]]  are not greater than their teacher. But the
        student who is fully trained will become like the teacher.  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:40 '
        content: 'Or <b>Disciples.</b>  '
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CAnd why worry about a speck in your friend\u2019s eye  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        when you have a log in your own?  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:41 '
        content: "  Greek   <b>your brother\u2019s eye; </b>  also in 6:42.  "
    - title: The Tree and Its Fruit
      content: "How can you think of saying, \u2018Friend,[[COMMENT(0)]]  let me
        help you get rid of that speck in your eye,\u2019 when you can\u2019t see
        past the log in your own eye? Hypocrite! First get rid of the log in your
        own eye; then you will see well enough to deal with the speck in your friend\u2019s
        eye.  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:42 '
        content: Greek <b>Brother.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CA good tree can\u2019t produce bad fruit, and a bad tree
        can\u2019t produce good fruit.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A tree is identified by its fruit. Figs are never gathered from thornbushes,
        and grapes are not picked from bramble bushes.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Building on a Solid Foundation
      content: 'A good person produces good things from the treasury of a good heart,
        and an evil person produces evil things from the treasury of an evil heart.
        What you say flows from what is in your heart.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CSo why do you keep calling me \u2018Lord, Lord!\u2019 when
        you don\u2019t do what I say?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will show you what it\u2019s like when someone comes to me, listens
        to my teaching, and then follows it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It is like a person building a house who digs deep and lays the foundation
        on solid rock. When the floodwaters rise and break against that house, it
        stands firm because it is well built.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Faith of a Roman Officer
      content: '  When Jesus had finished saying all this to the people, he returned
        to Capernaum. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'At that time the highly valued slave of a Roman officer[[COMMENT(0)]]
        was sick and near death. '
      comments:
      - number: '7:2 '
        content: Greek <b>a centurion; </b>similarly in 7:6.
    - title: 
      content: 'When the officer heard about Jesus, he sent some respected Jewish
        elders to ask him to come and heal his slave. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So they earnestly begged Jesus to help the man. \u201CIf anyone deserves
        your help, he does,\u201D they said, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201Cfor he loves the Jewish people and even built a synagogue for
        us.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So Jesus went with them. But just before they arrived at the house,
        the officer sent some friends to say, \u201CLord, don\u2019t trouble yourself
        by coming to my home, for I am not worthy of such an honor. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I am not even worthy to come and meet you. Just say the word from
        where you are, and my servant will be healed. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I know this because I am under the authority of my superior officers,
        and I have authority over my soldiers. I only need to say, \u2018Go,\u2019
        and they go, or \u2018Come,\u2019 and they come. And if I say to my slaves,
        \u2018Do this,\u2019 they do it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When Jesus heard this, he was amazed. Turning to the crowd that was
        following him, he said, \u201CI tell you, I haven\u2019t seen faith like
        this in all Israel!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: "Jesus Raises a Widow\u2019s Son"
      content: "And when the officer\u2019s friends returned to his house, they found
        the slave completely healed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Soon afterward Jesus went with his disciples to the village of Nain,
        and a large crowd followed him. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A funeral procession was coming out as he approached the village
        gate. The young man who had died was a widow\u2019s only son, and a large
        crowd from the village was with her. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When the Lord saw her, his heart overflowed with compassion. \u201CDon\u2019t
        cry!\u201D he said. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then he walked over to the coffin and touched it, and the bearers
        stopped. \u201CYoung man,\u201D he said, \u201CI tell you, get up.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the dead boy sat up and began to talk! And Jesus gave him back
        to his mother.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Great fear swept the crowd, and they praised God, saying, \u201CA
        mighty prophet has risen among us,\u201D and \u201CGod has visited his people
        today.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: Jesus and John the Baptist
      content: 'And the news about Jesus spread throughout Judea and the surrounding
        countryside.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The disciples of John the Baptist told John about everything Jesus
        was doing. So John called for two of his disciples, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "and he sent them to the Lord to ask him, \u201CAre you the Messiah
        we\u2019ve been expecting,[[COMMENT(0)]] or should we keep looking for someone
        else?\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:19 '
        content: Greek <b>Are you the one who is coming? </b>Also in 7:20.
    - title: 
      content: "John\u2019s two disciples found Jesus and said to him, \u201CJohn
        the Baptist sent us to ask, \u2018Are you the Messiah we\u2019ve been expecting,
        or should we keep looking for someone else?\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'At that very time, Jesus cured many people of their diseases, illnesses,
        and evil spirits, and he restored sight to many who were blind. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then he told John\u2019s disciples, \u201CGo back to John and tell
        him what you have seen and heard\u2014the blind see, the lame walk, those
        with leprosy are cured, the deaf hear, the dead are raised to life, and the
        Good News is being preached to the poor.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And he added, \u201CGod blesses those who do not fall away because
        of me.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:23 '
        content: 'Or <b>who are not offended by me.</b>  '
    - title: 
      content: "After John\u2019s disciples left, Jesus began talking about him to
        the crowds. \u201CWhat kind of man did you go into the wilderness to see?
        Was he a weak reed, swayed by every breath of wind?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Or were you expecting to see a man dressed in expensive clothes?
        No, people who wear beautiful clothes and live in luxury are found in palaces.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Were you looking for a prophet? Yes, and he is more than a prophet.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "John is the man to whom the Scriptures refer when they say,  \u2018Look,
        I am sending my messenger ahead of you,  and he will prepare your way before
        you.\u2019  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:27 '
        content: '  Mal 3:1.  '
    - title: 
      content: "  I tell you, of all who have ever lived, none is greater than John.
        Yet even the least person in the Kingdom of God is greater than he is!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When they heard this, all the people\u2014even the tax collectors\u2014agreed
        that God\u2019s way was right,[[COMMENT(0)]] for they had been baptized by
        John. "
      comments:
      - number: '7:29 '
        content: Or <b>praised God for his justice.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "But the Pharisees and experts in religious law rejected God\u2019s
        plan for them, for they had refused John\u2019s baptism.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CTo what can I compare the people of this generation?\u201D
        Jesus asked. \u201CHow can I describe them?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They are like children playing a game in the public square. They
        complain to their friends,  \u2018We played wedding songs,  and you didn\u2019t
        dance,  so we played funeral songs,  and you didn\u2019t weep.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  For John the Baptist didn\u2019t spend his time eating bread or
        drinking wine, and you say, \u2018He\u2019s possessed by a demon.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The Son of Man,[[COMMENT(0)]]  on the other hand, feasts and drinks,
        and you say, \u2018He\u2019s a glutton and a drunkard, and a friend of tax
        collectors and other sinners!\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:34 '
        content: "\u201CSon of Man\u201D is a title Jesus used for himself."
    - title: Jesus Anointed by a Sinful Woman
      content: "But wisdom is shown to be right by the lives of those who follow
        it.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:35 '
        content: Or <b>But wisdom is justified by all her children.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'One of the Pharisees asked Jesus to have dinner with him, so Jesus
        went to his home and sat down to eat.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '7:36 '
        content: Or <b>and reclined.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'When a certain immoral woman from that city heard he was eating there,
        she brought a beautiful alabaster jar filled with expensive perfume. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then she knelt behind him at his feet, weeping. Her tears fell on
        his feet, and she wiped them off with her hair. Then she kept kissing his
        feet and putting perfume on them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When the Pharisee who had invited him saw this, he said to himself,
        \u201CIf this man were a prophet, he would know what kind of woman is touching
        him. She\u2019s a sinner!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Jesus answered his thoughts. \u201CSimon,\u201D he said to the
        Pharisee, \u201CI have something to say to you.\u201D\u201CGo ahead, Teacher,\u201D
        Simon replied.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Jesus told him this story: \u201CA man loaned money to two people\u2014500
        pieces of silver[[COMMENT(0)]]  to one and 50 pieces to the other.  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:41 '
        content: "Greek <b>500 denarii. </b>A denarius was equivalent to a laborer\u2019s
          full day\u2019s wage."
    - title: 
      content: "But neither of them could repay him, so he kindly forgave them both,
        canceling their debts. Who do you suppose loved him more after that?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Simon answered, \u201CI suppose the one for whom he canceled the
        larger debt.\u201D  \u201CThat\u2019s right,\u201D Jesus said. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then he turned to the woman and said to Simon, \u201CLook at this
        woman kneeling here. When I entered your home, you didn\u2019t offer me water
        to wash the dust from my feet, but she has washed them with her tears and
        wiped them with her hair.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You didn\u2019t greet me with a kiss, but from the time I first came
        in, she has not stopped kissing my feet.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You neglected the courtesy of olive oil to anoint my head, but she
        has anointed my feet with rare perfume.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CI tell you, her sins\u2014and they are many\u2014have been
        forgiven, so she has shown me much love. But a person who is forgiven little
        shows only little love.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Jesus said to the woman, \u201CYour sins are forgiven.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The men at the table said among themselves, \u201CWho is this man,
        that he goes around forgiving sins?\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Women Who Followed Jesus
      content: '  Soon afterward Jesus began a tour of the nearby towns and villages,
        preaching and announcing the Good News about the Kingdom of God. He took
        his twelve disciples with him, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'along with some women who had been cured of evil spirits and diseases.
        Among them were Mary Magdalene, from whom he had cast out seven demons; '
      comments: []
    - title: Parable of the Farmer Scattering Seed
      content: "Joanna, the wife of Chuza, Herod\u2019s business manager; Susanna;
        and many others who were contributing from their own resources to support
        Jesus and his disciples.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'One day Jesus told a story in the form of a parable to a large crowd
        that had gathered from many towns to hear him: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CA farmer went out to plant his seed. As he scattered it across
        his field, some seed fell on a footpath, where it was stepped on, and the
        birds ate it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Other seed fell among rocks. It began to grow, but the plant soon
        wilted and died for lack of moisture.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Other seed fell among thorns that grew up with it and choked out
        the tender plants.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Still other seed fell on fertile soil. This seed grew and produced
        a crop that was a hundred times as much as had been planted!\u201D When he
        had said this, he called out, \u201CAnyone with ears to hear should listen
        and understand.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'His disciples asked him what this parable meant. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He replied, \u201CYou are permitted to understand the secrets[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        of the Kingdom of God. But I use parables to teach the others so that the
        Scriptures might be fulfilled:  \u2018When they look, they won\u2019t really
        see.  When they hear, they won\u2019t understand.\u2019  [[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:10a '
        content: 'Greek <b>mysteries.</b>  '
      - number: '8:10b '
        content: '  Isa 6:9 (Greek version).  '
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CThis is the meaning of the parable: The seed is God\u2019s
        word.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The seeds that fell on the footpath represent those who hear the
        message, only to have the devil come and take it away from their hearts and
        prevent them from believing and being saved.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The seeds on the rocky soil represent those who hear the message
        and receive it with joy. But since they don\u2019t have deep roots, they
        believe for a while, then they fall away when they face temptation.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The seeds that fell among the thorns represent those who hear the
        message, but all too quickly the message is crowded out by the cares and
        riches and pleasures of this life. And so they never grow into maturity.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Parable of the Lamp
      content: "And the seeds that fell on the good soil represent honest, good-hearted
        people who hear God\u2019s word, cling to it, and patiently produce a huge
        harvest.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CNo one lights a lamp and then covers it with a bowl or hides
        it under a bed. A lamp is placed on a stand, where its light can be seen
        by all who enter the house.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For all that is secret will eventually be brought into the open,
        and everything that is concealed will be brought to light and made known
        to all.  '
      comments: []
    - title: The True Family of Jesus
      content: "  \u201CSo pay attention to how you hear. To those who listen to
        my teaching, more understanding will be given. But for those who are not
        listening, even what they think they understand will be taken away from them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Jesus\u2019 mother and brothers came to see him, but they couldn\u2019t
        get to him because of the crowd. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Someone told Jesus, \u201CYour mother and your brothers are standing
        outside, and they want to see you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Jesus Calms the Storm
      content: "Jesus replied, \u201CMy mother and my brothers are all those who
        hear God\u2019s word and obey it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "One day Jesus said to his disciples, \u201CLet\u2019s cross to the
        other side of the lake.\u201D So they got into a boat and started out. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As they sailed across, Jesus settled down for a nap. But soon a fierce
        storm came down on the lake. The boat was filling with water, and they were
        in real danger.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The disciples went and woke him up, shouting, \u201CMaster, Master,
        we\u2019re going to drown!\u201DWhen Jesus woke up, he rebuked the wind and
        the raging waves. Suddenly the storm stopped and all was calm. "
      comments: []
    - title: Jesus Heals a Demon-Possessed Man
      content: "Then he asked them, \u201CWhere is your faith?\u201DThe disciples
        were terrified and amazed. \u201CWho is this man?\u201D they asked each other.
        \u201CWhen he gives a command, even the wind and waves obey him!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So they arrived in the region of the Gerasenes,[[COMMENT(0)]] across
        the lake from Galilee. '
      comments:
      - number: '8:26 '
        content: Other manuscripts read <b>Gadarenes; </b>still others read <b>Gergesenes;
          </b>also in 8:37. See Matt 8:28; Mark 5:1.
    - title: 
      content: 'As Jesus was climbing out of the boat, a man who was possessed by
        demons came out to meet him. For a long time he had been homeless and naked,
        living in the tombs outside the town.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As soon as he saw Jesus, he shrieked and fell down in front of him.
        Then he screamed, \u201CWhy are you interfering with me, Jesus, Son of the
        Most High God? Please, I beg you, don\u2019t torture me!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For Jesus had already commanded the evil[[COMMENT(0)]] spirit to
        come out of him. This spirit had often taken control of the man. Even when
        he was placed under guard and put in chains and shackles, he simply broke
        them and rushed out into the wilderness, completely under the demon\u2019s
        power.  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:29 '
        content: Greek <b>unclean.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Jesus demanded, \u201CWhat is your name?\u201D\u201CLegion,\u201D
        he replied, for he was filled with many demons. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The demons kept begging Jesus not to send them into the bottomless
        pit.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:31 '
        content: Or <b>the abyss, </b>or <b>the underworld.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'There happened to be a large herd of pigs feeding on the hillside
        nearby, and the demons begged him to let them enter into the pigs.So Jesus
        gave them permission. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the demons came out of the man and entered the pigs, and the
        entire herd plunged down the steep hillside into the lake and drowned.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When the herdsmen saw it, they fled to the nearby town and the surrounding
        countryside, spreading the news as they ran. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "People rushed out to see what had happened. A crowd soon gathered
        around Jesus, and they saw the man who had been freed from the demons. He
        was sitting at Jesus\u2019 feet, fully clothed and perfectly sane, and they
        were all afraid. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then those who had seen what happened told the others how the demon-possessed
        man had been healed. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And all the people in the region of the Gerasenes begged Jesus to
        go away and leave them alone, for a great wave of fear swept over them.So
        Jesus returned to the boat and left, crossing back to the other side of the
        lake. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The man who had been freed from the demons begged to go with him.
        But Jesus sent him home, saying, '
      comments: []
    - title: Jesus Heals in Response to Faith
      content: "\u201CNo, go back to your family, and tell them everything God has
        done for you.\u201D So he went all through the town proclaiming the great
        things Jesus had done for him.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'On the other side of the lake the crowds welcomed Jesus, because
        they had been waiting for him. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then a man named Jairus, a leader of the local synagogue, came and
        fell at Jesus\u2019 feet, pleading with him to come home with him. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'His only daughter,[[COMMENT(0)]] who was about twelve years old,
        was dying.As Jesus went with him, he was surrounded by the crowds. '
      comments:
      - number: '8:42 '
        content: Or <b>His only child, a daughter.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'A woman in the crowd had suffered for twelve years with constant
        bleeding,[[COMMENT(0)]] and she could find no cure. '
      comments:
      - number: '8:43 '
        content: Some manuscripts add <b>having spent everything she had on doctors.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Coming up behind Jesus, she touched the fringe of his robe. Immediately,
        the bleeding stopped.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CWho touched me?\u201D Jesus asked.Everyone denied it, and
        Peter said, \u201CMaster, this whole crowd is pressing up against you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But Jesus said, \u201CSomeone deliberately touched me, for I felt
        healing power go out from me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When the woman realized that she could not stay hidden, she began
        to tremble and fell to her knees in front of him. The whole crowd heard her
        explain why she had touched him and that she had been immediately healed. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CDaughter,\u201D he said to her, \u201Cyour faith has made you
        well. Go in peace.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "While he was still speaking to her, a messenger arrived from the
        home of Jairus, the leader of the synagogue. He told him, \u201CYour daughter
        is dead. There\u2019s no use troubling the Teacher now.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But when Jesus heard what had happened, he said to Jairus, \u201CDon\u2019t
        be afraid. Just have faith, and she will be healed.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When they arrived at the house, Jesus wouldn\u2019t let anyone go
        in with him except Peter, John, James, and the little girl\u2019s father
        and mother. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The house was filled with people weeping and wailing, but he said,
        \u201CStop the weeping! She isn\u2019t dead; she\u2019s only asleep.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But the crowd laughed at him because they all knew she had died. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Jesus took her by the hand and said in a loud voice, \u201CMy
        child, get up!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And at that moment her life[[COMMENT(0)]] returned, and she immediately
        stood up! Then Jesus told them to give her something to eat. '
      comments:
      - number: '8:55 '
        content: Or <b>her spirit.</b>
  - verses:
    - title: Jesus Sends Out the Twelve Disciples
      content: '  One day Jesus called together his twelve disciples[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and gave them power and authority to cast out all demons and to heal all
        diseases. '
      comments:
      - number: '9:1 '
        content: Greek <b>the Twelve; </b>other manuscripts read <b>the twelve apostles.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Then he sent them out to tell everyone about the Kingdom of God and
        to heal the sick. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTake nothing for your journey,\u201D he instructed them. \u201CDon\u2019t
        take a walking stick, a traveler\u2019s bag, food, money,[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        or even a change of clothes.  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:3 '
        content: Or <b>silver coins.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Wherever you go, stay in the same house until you leave town.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And if a town refuses to welcome you, shake its dust from your feet
        as you leave to show that you have abandoned those people to their fate.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: "Herod\u2019s Confusion"
      content: 'So they began their circuit of the villages, preaching the Good News
        and healing the sick.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When Herod Antipas, the ruler of Galilee,[[COMMENT(0)]] heard about
        everything Jesus was doing, he was puzzled. Some were saying that John the
        Baptist had been raised from the dead. '
      comments:
      - number: '9:7 '
        content: Greek <b>Herod the tetrarch. </b>Herod Antipas was a son of King
          Herod and was ruler over Galilee.
    - title: 
      content: 'Others thought Jesus was Elijah or one of the other prophets risen
        from the dead.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Jesus Feeds Five Thousand
      content: "\u201CI beheaded John,\u201D Herod said, \u201Cso who is this man
        about whom I hear such stories?\u201D And he kept trying to see him.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When the apostles returned, they told Jesus everything they had done.
        Then he slipped quietly away with them toward the town of Bethsaida. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But the crowds found out where he was going, and they followed him.
        He welcomed them and taught them about the Kingdom of God, and he healed
        those who were sick.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Late in the afternoon the twelve disciples came to him and said,
        \u201CSend the crowds away to the nearby villages and farms, so they can
        find food and lodging for the night. There is nothing to eat here in this
        remote place.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But Jesus said, \u201CYou feed them.\u201D\u201CBut we have only
        five loaves of bread and two fish,\u201D they answered. \u201COr are you
        expecting us to go and buy enough food for this whole crowd?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For there were about 5,000 men there.Jesus replied, \u201CTell them
        to sit down in groups of about fifty each.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So the people all sat down. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Jesus took the five loaves and two fish, looked up toward heaven,
        and blessed them. Then, breaking the loaves into pieces, he kept giving the
        bread and fish to the disciples so they could distribute it to the people. '
      comments: []
    - title: "Peter\u2019s Declaration about Jesus"
      content: 'They all ate as much as they wanted, and afterward, the disciples
        picked up twelve baskets of leftovers!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "One day Jesus left the crowds to pray alone. Only his disciples were
        with him, and he asked them, \u201CWho do people say I am?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWell,\u201D they replied, \u201Csome say John the Baptist,
        some say Elijah, and others say you are one of the other ancient prophets
        risen from the dead.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Jesus Predicts His Death
      content: "Then he asked them, \u201CBut who do you say I am?\u201DPeter replied,
        \u201CYou are the Messiah[[COMMENT(0)]] sent from God!\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:20 '
        content: "Or <b>the Christ. </b><b>Messiah </b>(a Hebrew term) and <b>Christ
          </b>(a Greek term) both mean \u201Canointed one.\u201D"
    - title: 
      content: 'Jesus warned his disciples not to tell anyone who he was. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe Son of Man[[COMMENT(0)]]  must suffer many terrible things,\u201D
        he said. \u201CHe will be rejected by the elders, the leading priests, and
        the teachers of religious law. He will be killed, but on the third day he
        will be raised from the dead.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:22 '
        content: "\u201CSon of Man\u201D is a title Jesus used for himself."
    - title: 
      content: "Then he said to the crowd, \u201CIf any of you wants to be my follower,
        you must give up your own way, take up your cross daily, and follow me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If you try to hang on to your life, you will lose it. But if you
        give up your life for my sake, you will save it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And what do you benefit if you gain the whole world but are yourself
        lost or destroyed?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If anyone is ashamed of me and my message, the Son of Man will be
        ashamed of that person when he returns in his glory and in the glory of the
        Father and the holy angels.  '
      comments: []
    - title: The Transfiguration
      content: "I tell you the truth, some standing here right now will not die before
        they see the Kingdom of God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'About eight days later Jesus took Peter, John, and James up on a
        mountain to pray. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And as he was praying, the appearance of his face was transformed,
        and his clothes became dazzling white. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Suddenly, two men, Moses and Elijah, appeared and began talking with
        Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They were glorious to see. And they were speaking about his exodus
        from this world, which was about to be fulfilled in Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Peter and the others had fallen asleep. When they woke up, they saw
        Jesus\u2019 glory and the two men standing with him. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As Moses and Elijah were starting to leave, Peter, not even knowing
        what he was saying, blurted out, \u201CMaster, it\u2019s wonderful for us
        to be here! Let\u2019s make three shelters as memorials[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014one
        for you, one for Moses, and one for Elijah.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '9:33 '
        content: Greek <b>three tabernacles.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'But even as he was saying this, a cloud overshadowed them, and terror
        gripped them as the cloud covered them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then a voice from the cloud said, \u201CThis is my Son, my Chosen
        One.[[COMMENT(0)]] Listen to him.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '9:35 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>This is my dearly loved Son.</b>
    - title: Jesus Heals a Demon-Possessed Boy
      content: "When the voice finished, Jesus was there alone. They didn\u2019t
        tell anyone at that time what they had seen.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The next day, after they had come down the mountain, a large crowd
        met Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A man in the crowd called out to him, \u201CTeacher, I beg you to
        look at my son, my only child. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'An evil spirit keeps seizing him, making him scream. It throws him
        into convulsions so that he foams at the mouth. It batters him and hardly
        ever leaves him alone. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I begged your disciples to cast out the spirit, but they couldn\u2019t
        do it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Jesus said, \u201CYou faithless and corrupt people! How long must
        I be with you and put up with you?\u201D Then he said to the man, \u201CBring
        your son here.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As the boy came forward, the demon knocked him to the ground and
        threw him into a violent convulsion. But Jesus rebuked the evil[[COMMENT(0)]]
        spirit and healed the boy. Then he gave him back to his father. '
      comments:
      - number: '9:42 '
        content: Greek <b>unclean.</b>
    - title: Jesus Again Predicts His Death
      content: "Awe gripped the people as they saw this majestic display of God\u2019s
        power.While everyone was marveling at everything he was doing, Jesus said
        to his disciples, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CListen to me and remember what I say. The Son of Man is going
        to be betrayed into the hands of his enemies.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: The Greatest in the Kingdom
      content: "But they didn\u2019t know what he meant. Its significance was hidden
        from them, so they couldn\u2019t understand it, and they were afraid to ask
        him about it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then his disciples began arguing about which of them was the greatest. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But Jesus knew their thoughts, so he brought a little child to his
        side. '
      comments: []
    - title: Using the Name of Jesus
      content: "Then he said to them, \u201CAnyone who welcomes a little child like
        this on my behalf[[COMMENT(0)]]  welcomes me, and anyone who welcomes me
        also welcomes my Father who sent me. Whoever is the least among you is the
        greatest.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:48 '
        content: Greek <b>in my name.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "John said to Jesus, \u201CMaster, we saw someone using your name
        to cast out demons, but we told him to stop because he isn\u2019t in our
        group.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Opposition from Samaritans
      content: "But Jesus said, \u201CDon\u2019t stop him! Anyone who is not against
        you is for you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As the time drew near for him to ascend to heaven, Jesus resolutely
        set out for Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He sent messengers ahead to a Samaritan village to prepare for his
        arrival. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But the people of the village did not welcome Jesus because he was
        on his way to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When James and John saw this, they said to Jesus, \u201CLord, should
        we call down fire from heaven to burn them up[[COMMENT(0)]]?\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '9:54 '
        content: Some manuscripts add <b>as Elijah did.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'But Jesus turned and rebuked them.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:55 '
        content: "Some manuscripts add an expanded conclusion to verse 55 and an
          additional sentence in verse 56: <b>And he said, \u201CYou don\u2019t realize
          what your hearts are like. </b><b>For the Son of Man has not come to destroy
          people\u2019s lives, but to save them.\u201D</b>"
    - title: The Cost of Following Jesus
      content: 'So they went on to another village.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As they were walking along, someone said to Jesus, \u201CI will follow
        you wherever you go.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But Jesus replied, \u201CFoxes have dens to live in, and birds have
        nests, but the Son of Man has no place even to lay his head.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He said to another person, \u201CCome, follow me.\u201DThe man agreed,
        but he said, \u201CLord, first let me return home and bury my father.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But Jesus told him, \u201CLet the spiritually dead bury their own
        dead![[COMMENT(0)]]  Your duty is to go and preach about the Kingdom of God.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:60 '
        content: Greek <b>Let the dead bury their own dead.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Another said, \u201CYes, Lord, I will follow you, but first let me
        say good-bye to my family.\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Jesus Sends Out His Disciples
      content: '  The Lord now chose seventy-two[[COMMENT(0)]] other disciples and
        sent them ahead in pairs to all the towns and places he planned to visit. '
      comments:
      - number: '10:1 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>seventy; </b>also in 10:17.
    - title: 
      content: "These were his instructions to them: \u201CThe harvest is great,
        but the workers are few. So pray to the Lord who is in charge of the harvest;
        ask him to send more workers into his fields.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Now go, and remember that I am sending you out as lambs among wolves.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t take any money with you, nor a traveler\u2019s bag, nor
        an extra pair of sandals. And don\u2019t stop to greet anyone on the road.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CWhenever you enter someone\u2019s home, first say, \u2018May
        God\u2019s peace be on this house.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If those who live there are peaceful, the blessing will stand; if
        they are not, the blessing will return to you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t move around from home to home. Stay in one place, eating
        and drinking what they provide. Don\u2019t hesitate to accept hospitality,
        because those who work deserve their pay.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CIf you enter a town and it welcomes you, eat whatever is
        set before you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Heal the sick, and tell them, \u2018The Kingdom of God is near you
        now.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But if a town refuses to welcome you, go out into its streets and
        say,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018We wipe even the dust of your town from our feet to show that
        we have abandoned you to your fate. And know this\u2014the Kingdom of God
        is near!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I assure you, even wicked Sodom will be better off than such a town
        on judgment day.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CWhat sorrow awaits you, Korazin and Bethsaida! For if the
        miracles I did in you had been done in wicked Tyre and Sidon, their people
        would have repented of their sins long ago, clothing themselves in burlap
        and throwing ashes on their heads to show their remorse.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yes, Tyre and Sidon will be better off on judgment day than you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And you people of Capernaum, will you be honored in heaven? No, you
        will go down to the place of the dead.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:15 '
        content: Greek <b>to Hades.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Then he said to the disciples, \u201CAnyone who accepts your message
        is also accepting me. And anyone who rejects you is rejecting me. And anyone
        who rejects me is rejecting God, who sent me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When the seventy-two disciples returned, they joyfully reported to
        him, \u201CLord, even the demons obey us when we use your name!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CYes,\u201D he told them, \u201CI saw Satan fall from heaven
        like lightning!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Look, I have given you authority over all the power of the enemy,
        and you can walk among snakes and scorpions and crush them. Nothing will
        injure you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: "Jesus\u2019 Prayer of Thanksgiving"
      content: "But don\u2019t rejoice because evil spirits obey you; rejoice because
        your names are registered in heaven.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "At that same time Jesus was filled with the joy of the Holy Spirit,
        and he said, \u201CO Father, Lord of heaven and earth, thank you for hiding
        these things from those who think themselves wise and clever, and for revealing
        them to the childlike. Yes, Father, it pleased you to do it this way.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CMy Father has entrusted everything to me. No one truly knows
        the Son except the Father, and no one truly knows the Father except the Son
        and those to whom the Son chooses to reveal him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then when they were alone, he turned to the disciples and said, \u201CBlessed
        are the eyes that see what you have seen.  "
      comments: []
    - title: The Most Important Commandment
      content: "I tell you, many prophets and kings longed to see what you see, but
        they didn\u2019t see it. And they longed to hear what you hear, but they
        didn\u2019t hear it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "One day an expert in religious law stood up to test Jesus by asking
        him this question: \u201CTeacher, what should I do to inherit eternal life?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Jesus replied, \u201CWhat does the law of Moses say? How do you read
        it?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The man answered, \u201C\u2018You must love the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God with all your heart, all your soul, all your strength, and all your
        mind.\u2019 And, \u2018Love your neighbor as yourself.\u2019\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:27 '
        content: Deut 6:5; Lev 19:18.
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CRight!\u201D Jesus told him. \u201CDo this and you will live!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Parable of the Good Samaritan
      content: "The man wanted to justify his actions, so he asked Jesus, \u201CAnd
        who is my neighbor?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Jesus replied with a story: \u201CA Jewish man was traveling from
        Jerusalem down to Jericho, and he was attacked by bandits. They stripped
        him of his clothes, beat him up, and left him half dead beside the road.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CBy chance a priest came along. But when he saw the man lying
        there, he crossed to the other side of the road and passed him by.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A Temple assistant[[COMMENT(0)]]  walked over and looked at him lying
        there, but he also passed by on the other side.  '
      comments:
      - number: '10:32 '
        content: Greek <b>A Levite.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CThen a despised Samaritan came along, and when he saw the
        man, he felt compassion for him.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Going over to him, the Samaritan soothed his wounds with olive oil
        and wine and bandaged them. Then he put the man on his own donkey and took
        him to an inn, where he took care of him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The next day he handed the innkeeper two silver coins,[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        telling him, \u2018Take care of this man. If his bill runs higher than this,
        I\u2019ll pay you the next time I\u2019m here.\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:35 '
        content: "Greek <b>two denarii. </b>A denarius was equivalent to a laborer\u2019s
          full day\u2019s wage."
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CNow which of these three would you say was a neighbor to
        the man who was attacked by bandits?\u201D Jesus asked.  "
      comments: []
    - title: Jesus Visits Martha and Mary
      content: "The man replied, \u201CThe one who showed him mercy.\u201DThen Jesus
        said, \u201CYes, now go and do the same.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As Jesus and the disciples continued on their way to Jerusalem, they
        came to a certain village where a woman named Martha welcomed him into her
        home. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Her sister, Mary, sat at the Lord\u2019s feet, listening to what
        he taught. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But Martha was distracted by the big dinner she was preparing. She
        came to Jesus and said, \u201CLord, doesn\u2019t it seem unfair to you that
        my sister just sits here while I do all the work? Tell her to come and help
        me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But the Lord said to her, \u201CMy dear Martha, you are worried and
        upset over all these details!  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Teaching about Prayer
      content: "  Once Jesus was in a certain place praying. As he finished, one
        of his disciples came to him and said, \u201CLord, teach us to pray, just
        as John taught his disciples.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Jesus said, \u201CThis is how you should pray:[[COMMENT(0)]]  \u201CFather,
        may your name be kept holy.  May your Kingdom come soon.  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:2 '
        content: "Some manuscripts add additional phrases from the Lord\u2019s Prayer
          as it reads in Matt 6:9-13.  "
    - title: 
      content: '  Give us each day the food we need,  [[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:3 '
        content: '  Or   <b>Give us each day our food for the day; </b>  or   <b>Give
          us each day our food for tomorrow.</b>    '
    - title: 
      content: "  and forgive us our sins,  as we forgive those who sin against us. 
        And don\u2019t let us yield to temptation.  [[COMMENT(0)]]  \u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:4 '
        content: '  Or   <b>And keep us from being tested.</b>  '
    - title: 
      content: "Then, teaching them more about prayer, he used this story: \u201CSuppose
        you went to a friend\u2019s house at midnight, wanting to borrow three loaves
        of bread. You say to him,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018A friend of mine has just arrived for a visit, and I have nothing
        for him to eat.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And suppose he calls out from his bedroom, \u2018Don\u2019t bother
        me. The door is locked for the night, and my family and I are all in bed.
        I can\u2019t help you.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But I tell you this\u2014though he won\u2019t do it for friendship\u2019s
        sake, if you keep knocking long enough, he will get up and give you whatever
        you need because of your shameless persistence.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:8 '
        content: "Or <b>in order to avoid shame, </b>or <b>so his reputation won\u2019t
          be damaged.</b>  "
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CAnd so I tell you, keep on asking, and you will receive what
        you ask for. Keep on seeking, and you will find. Keep on knocking, and the
        door will be opened to you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For everyone who asks, receives. Everyone who seeks, finds. And to
        everyone who knocks, the door will be opened.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CYou fathers\u2014if your children ask  [[COMMENT(0)]]  for
        a fish, do you give them a snake instead?  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:11 '
        content: '  Some manuscripts add   <b>for bread, do you give them a stone?
          Or [if they ask].</b>  '
    - title: 
      content: 'Or if they ask for an egg, do you give them a scorpion? Of course
        not!  '
      comments: []
    - title: Jesus and the Prince of Demons
      content: "So if you sinful people know how to give good gifts to your children,
        how much more will your heavenly Father give the Holy Spirit to those who
        ask him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "One day Jesus cast out a demon from a man who couldn\u2019t speak,
        and when the demon was gone, the man began to speak. The crowds were amazed, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "but some of them said, \u201CNo wonder he can cast out demons. He
        gets his power from Satan,[[COMMENT(0)]] the prince of demons.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '11:15 '
        content: Greek <b>Beelzeboul; </b>also in 11:18, 19. Other manuscripts read
          <b>Beezeboul; </b>Latin version reads <b>Beelzebub.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Others, trying to test Jesus, demanded that he show them a miraculous
        sign from heaven to prove his authority.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He knew their thoughts, so he said, \u201CAny kingdom divided by
        civil war is doomed. A family splintered by feuding will fall apart.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You say I am empowered by Satan. But if Satan is divided and fighting
        against himself, how can his kingdom survive?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And if I am empowered by Satan, what about your own exorcists? They
        cast out demons, too, so they will condemn you for what you have said.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But if I am casting out demons by the power of God,[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        then the Kingdom of God has arrived among you.  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:20 '
        content: 'Greek <b>by the finger of God.</b>  '
    - title: 
      content: "For when a strong man is fully armed and guards his palace, his possessions
        are safe\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'until someone even stronger attacks and overpowers him, strips him
        of his weapons, and carries off his belongings.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CAnyone who isn\u2019t with me opposes me, and anyone who
        isn\u2019t working with me is actually working against me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CWhen an evil  [[COMMENT(0)]]  spirit leaves a person, it
        goes into the desert, searching for rest. But when it finds none, it says,
        \u2018I will return to the person I came from.\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:24 '
        content: '  Greek   <b>unclean.</b>  '
    - title: 
      content: 'So it returns and finds that its former home is all swept and in
        order.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the spirit finds seven other spirits more evil than itself,
        and they all enter the person and live there. And so that person is worse
        off than before.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As he was speaking, a woman in the crowd called out, \u201CGod bless
        your mother\u2014the womb from which you came, and the breasts that nursed
        you!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: The Sign of Jonah
      content: "Jesus replied, \u201CBut even more blessed are all who hear the word
        of God and put it into practice.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As the crowd pressed in on Jesus, he said, \u201CThis evil generation
        keeps asking me to show them a miraculous sign. But the only sign I will
        give them is the sign of Jonah.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'What happened to him was a sign to the people of Nineveh that God
        had sent him. What happens to the Son of Man[[COMMENT(0)]]  will be a sign
        to these people that he was sent by God.  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:30 '
        content: "\u201CSon of Man\u201D is a title Jesus used for himself.  "
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CThe queen of Sheba  [[COMMENT(0)]]  will stand up against
        this generation on judgment day and condemn it, for she came from a distant
        land to hear the wisdom of Solomon. Now someone greater than Solomon is here\u2014but
        you refuse to listen.  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:31 '
        content: '  Greek   <b>The queen of the south.</b>    '
    - title: Receiving the Light
      content: "The people of Nineveh will also stand up against this generation
        on judgment day and condemn it, for they repented of their sins at the preaching
        of Jonah. Now someone greater than Jonah is here\u2014but you refuse to repent.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CNo one lights a lamp and then hides it or puts it under a
        basket.  [[COMMENT(0)]]  Instead, a lamp is placed on a stand, where its
        light can be seen by all who enter the house.  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:33 '
        content: '  Some manuscripts do not include   <b>or puts it under a basket.</b>  '
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CYour eye is like a lamp that provides light for your body.
        When your eye is healthy, your whole body is filled with light. But when
        it is unhealthy, your body is filled with darkness.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Make sure that the light you think you have is not actually darkness.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Jesus Criticizes the Religious Leaders
      content: "If you are filled with light, with no dark corners, then your whole
        life will be radiant, as though a floodlight were filling you with light.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As Jesus was speaking, one of the Pharisees invited him home for
        a meal. So he went in and took his place at the table.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:37 '
        content: 'Or <b>and reclined.</b>  '
    - title: 
      content: 'His host was amazed to see that he sat down to eat without first
        performing the hand-washing ceremony required by Jewish custom. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the Lord said to him, \u201CYou Pharisees are so careful to
        clean the outside of the cup and the dish, but inside you are filthy\u2014full
        of greed and wickedness!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Fools! Didn\u2019t God make the inside as well as the outside?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So clean the inside by giving gifts to the poor, and you will be
        clean all over.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CWhat sorrow awaits you Pharisees! For you are careful to
        tithe even the tiniest income from your herb gardens,  [[COMMENT(0)]]  but
        you ignore justice and the love of God. You should tithe, yes, but do not
        neglect the more important things.  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:42 '
        content: '  Greek   <b>tithe the mint, the rue, and every herb.</b>  '
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CWhat sorrow awaits you Pharisees! For you love to sit in
        the seats of honor in the synagogues and receive respectful greetings as
        you walk in the marketplaces.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yes, what sorrow awaits you! For you are like hidden graves in a
        field. People walk over them without knowing the corruption they are stepping
        on.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTeacher,\u201D said an expert in religious law, \u201Cyou have
        insulted us, too, in what you just said.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CYes,\u201D said Jesus, \u201Cwhat sorrow also awaits you
        experts in religious law! For you crush people with unbearable religious
        demands, and you never lift a finger to ease the burden.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'What sorrow awaits you! For you build monuments for the prophets
        your own ancestors killed long ago.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But in fact, you stand as witnesses who agree with what your ancestors
        did. They killed the prophets, and you join in their crime by building the
        monuments!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This is what God in his wisdom said about you:[[COMMENT(0)]]  \u2018I
        will send prophets and apostles to them, but they will kill some and persecute
        the others.\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '11:49 '
        content: Greek <b>Therefore, the wisdom of God said.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CAs a result, this generation will be held responsible for
        the murder of all God\u2019s prophets from the creation of the world\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'from the murder of Abel to the murder of Zechariah, who was killed
        between the altar and the sanctuary. Yes, it will certainly be charged against
        this generation.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CWhat sorrow awaits you experts in religious law! For you
        remove the key to knowledge from the people. You don\u2019t enter the Kingdom
        yourselves, and you prevent others from entering.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As Jesus was leaving, the teachers of religious law and the Pharisees
        became hostile and tried to provoke him with many questions. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Warning against Hypocrisy
      content: "  Meanwhile, the crowds grew until thousands were milling about and
        stepping on each other. Jesus turned first to his disciples and warned them,
        \u201CBeware of the yeast of the Pharisees\u2014their hypocrisy.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The time is coming when everything that is covered up will be revealed,
        and all that is secret will be made known to all.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Whatever you have said in the dark will be heard in the light, and
        what you have whispered behind closed doors will be shouted from the housetops
        for all to hear!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CDear friends, don\u2019t be afraid of those who want to kill
        your body; they cannot do any more to you after that.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But I\u2019ll tell you whom to fear. Fear God, who has the power
        to kill you and then throw you into hell.[[COMMENT(0)]]  Yes, he\u2019s the
        one to fear.  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:5 '
        content: 'Greek <b>Gehenna.</b>  '
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CWhat is the price of five sparrows\u2014two copper coins 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  ? Yet God does not forget a single one of them.  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:6 '
        content: '  Greek   <b>two assaria </b>  [Roman coins equal to 1/16 of a
          denarius].    '
    - title: 
      content: "And the very hairs on your head are all numbered. So don\u2019t be
        afraid; you are more valuable to God than a whole flock of sparrows.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CI tell you the truth, everyone who acknowledges me publicly
        here on earth, the Son of Man  [[COMMENT(0)]]  will also acknowledge in the
        presence of God\u2019s angels.  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:8 '
        content: "  \u201CSon of Man\u201D is a title Jesus used for himself.  "
    - title: 
      content: "But anyone who denies me here on earth will be denied before God\u2019s
        angels.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Anyone who speaks against the Son of Man can be forgiven, but anyone
        who blasphemes the Holy Spirit will not be forgiven.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CAnd when you are brought to trial in the synagogues and before
        rulers and authorities, don\u2019t worry about how to defend yourself or
        what to say,  "
      comments: []
    - title: Parable of the Rich Fool
      content: "for the Holy Spirit will teach you at that time what needs to be
        said.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then someone called from the crowd, \u201CTeacher, please tell my
        brother to divide our father\u2019s estate with me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Jesus replied, \u201CFriend, who made me a judge over you to decide
        such things as that?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then he said, \u201CBeware! Guard against every kind of greed. Life
        is not measured by how much you own.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then he told them a story: \u201CA rich man had a fertile farm that
        produced fine crops.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He said to himself, \u2018What should I do? I don\u2019t have room
        for all my crops.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then he said, \u2018I know! I\u2019ll tear down my barns and build
        bigger ones. Then I\u2019ll have room enough to store all my wheat and other
        goods.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And I\u2019ll sit back and say to myself, \u201CMy friend, you have
        enough stored away for years to come. Now take it easy! Eat, drink, and be
        merry!\u201D\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CBut God said to him, \u2018You fool! You will die this very
        night. Then who will get everything you worked for?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: Teaching about Money and Possessions
      content: "  \u201CYes, a person is a fool to store up earthly wealth but not
        have a rich relationship with God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then, turning to his disciples, Jesus said, \u201CThat is why I tell
        you not to worry about everyday life\u2014whether you have enough food to
        eat or enough clothes to wear.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For life is more than food, and your body more than clothing.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Look at the ravens. They don\u2019t plant or harvest or store food
        in barns, for God feeds them. And you are far more valuable to him than any
        birds!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Can all your worries add a single moment to your life?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And if worry can\u2019t accomplish a little thing like that, what\u2019s
        the use of worrying over bigger things?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CLook at the lilies and how they grow. They don\u2019t work
        or make their clothing, yet Solomon in all his glory was not dressed as beautifully
        as they are.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And if God cares so wonderfully for flowers that are here today and
        thrown into the fire tomorrow, he will certainly care for you. Why do you
        have so little faith?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CAnd don\u2019t be concerned about what to eat and what to
        drink. Don\u2019t worry about such things.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'These things dominate the thoughts of unbelievers all over the world,
        but your Father already knows your needs.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Seek the Kingdom of God above all else, and he will give you everything
        you need.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CSo don\u2019t be afraid, little flock. For it gives your
        Father great happiness to give you the Kingdom.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CSell your possessions and give to those in need. This will
        store up treasure for you in heaven! And the purses of heaven never get old
        or develop holes. Your treasure will be safe; no thief can steal it and no
        moth can destroy it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: "Be Ready for the Lord\u2019s Coming"
      content: 'Wherever your treasure is, there the desires of your heart will also
        be.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CBe dressed for service and keep your lamps burning,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'as though you were waiting for your master to return from the wedding
        feast. Then you will be ready to open the door and let him in the moment
        he arrives and knocks.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The servants who are ready and waiting for his return will be rewarded.
        I tell you the truth, he himself will seat them, put on an apron, and serve
        them as they sit and eat!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He may come in the middle of the night or just before dawn.[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        But whenever he comes, he will reward the servants who are ready.  '
      comments:
      - number: '12:38 '
        content: 'Greek <b>in the second or third watch.</b>  '
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CUnderstand this: If a homeowner knew exactly when a burglar
        was coming, he would not permit his house to be broken into.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You also must be ready all the time, for the Son of Man will come
        when least expected.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Peter asked, \u201CLord, is that illustration just for us or for
        everyone?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And the Lord replied, \u201CA faithful, sensible servant is one to
        whom the master can give the responsibility of managing his other household
        servants and feeding them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If the master returns and finds that the servant has done a good
        job, there will be a reward.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I tell you the truth, the master will put that servant in charge
        of all he owns.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But what if the servant thinks, \u2018My master won\u2019t be back
        for a while,\u2019 and he begins beating the other servants, partying, and
        getting drunk?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The master will return unannounced and unexpected, and he will cut
        the servant in pieces and banish him with the unfaithful.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CAnd a servant who knows what the master wants, but isn\u2019t
        prepared and doesn\u2019t carry out those instructions, will be severely
        punished.  "
      comments: []
    - title: Jesus Causes Division
      content: 'But someone who does not know, and then does something wrong, will
        be punished only lightly. When someone has been given much, much will be
        required in return; and when someone has been entrusted with much, even more
        will be required.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CI have come to set the world on fire, and I wish it were
        already burning!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I have a terrible baptism of suffering ahead of me, and I am under
        a heavy burden until it is accomplished.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do you think I have come to bring peace to the earth? No, I have
        come to divide people against each other!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "From now on families will be split apart, three in favor of me, and
        two against\u2014or two in favor and three against.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u2018Father will be divided against son  and son against father; 
        mother against daughter  and daughter against mother;  and mother-in-law
        against daughter-in-law  and daughter-in-law against mother-in-law.\u2019 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  \u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '12:53 '
        content: '  Mic 7:6.  '
    - title: 
      content: "Then Jesus turned to the crowd and said, \u201CWhen you see clouds
        beginning to form in the west, you say, \u2018Here comes a shower.\u2019
        And you are right.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When the south wind blows, you say, \u2018Today will be a scorcher.\u2019
        And it is.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You fools! You know how to interpret the weather signs of the earth
        and sky, but you don\u2019t know how to interpret the present times.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CWhy can\u2019t you decide for yourselves what is right?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When you are on the way to court with your accuser, try to settle
        the matter before you get there. Otherwise, your accuser may drag you before
        the judge, who will hand you over to an officer, who will throw you into
        prison.  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Call to Repentance
      content: '  About this time Jesus was informed that Pilate had murdered some
        people from Galilee as they were offering sacrifices at the Temple. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CDo you think those Galileans were worse sinners than all the
        other people from Galilee?\u201D Jesus asked. \u201CIs that why they suffered?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Not at all! And you will perish, too, unless you repent of your sins
        and turn to God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And what about the eighteen people who died when the tower in Siloam
        fell on them? Were they the worst sinners in Jerusalem?  '
      comments: []
    - title: Parable of the Barren Fig Tree
      content: "No, and I tell you again that unless you repent, you will perish,
        too.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Jesus told this story: \u201CA man planted a fig tree in his
        garden and came again and again to see if there was any fruit on it, but
        he was always disappointed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Finally, he said to his gardener, \u2018I\u2019ve waited three years,
        and there hasn\u2019t been a single fig! Cut it down. It\u2019s just taking
        up space in the garden.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CThe gardener answered, \u2018Sir, give it one more chance.
        Leave it another year, and I\u2019ll give it special attention and plenty
        of fertilizer.  "
      comments: []
    - title: Jesus Heals on the Sabbath
      content: "If we get figs next year, fine. If not, then you can cut it down.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'One Sabbath day as Jesus was teaching in a synagogue, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'he saw a woman who had been crippled by an evil spirit. She had been
        bent double for eighteen years and was unable to stand up straight. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When Jesus saw her, he called her over and said, \u201CDear woman,
        you are healed of your sickness!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then he touched her, and instantly she could stand straight. How
        she praised God!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But the leader in charge of the synagogue was indignant that Jesus
        had healed her on the Sabbath day. \u201CThere are six days of the week for
        working,\u201D he said to the crowd. \u201CCome on those days to be healed,
        not on the Sabbath.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But the Lord replied, \u201CYou hypocrites! Each of you works on
        the Sabbath day! Don\u2019t you untie your ox or your donkey from its stall
        on the Sabbath and lead it out for water?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This dear woman, a daughter of Abraham, has been held in bondage
        by Satan for eighteen years. Isn\u2019t it right that she be released, even
        on the Sabbath?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Parable of the Mustard Seed
      content: 'This shamed his enemies, but all the people rejoiced at the wonderful
        things he did.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Jesus said, \u201CWhat is the Kingdom of God like? How can I
        illustrate it?  "
      comments: []
    - title: Parable of the Yeast
      content: "It is like a tiny mustard seed that a man planted in a garden; it
        grows and becomes a tree, and the birds make nests in its branches.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He also asked, \u201CWhat else is the Kingdom of God like?  "
      comments: []
    - title: The Narrow Door
      content: "It is like the yeast a woman used in making bread. Even though she
        put only a little yeast in three measures of flour, it permeated every part
        of the dough.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Jesus went through the towns and villages, teaching as he went, always
        pressing on toward Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Someone asked him, \u201CLord, will only a few be saved?\u201DHe
        replied, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWork hard to enter the narrow door to God\u2019s Kingdom, for
        many will try to enter but will fail.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When the master of the house has locked the door, it will be too
        late. You will stand outside knocking and pleading, \u2018Lord, open the
        door for us!\u2019 But he will reply, \u2018I don\u2019t know you or where
        you come from.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then you will say, \u2018But we ate and drank with you, and you taught
        in our streets.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And he will reply, \u2018I tell you, I don\u2019t know you or where
        you come from. Get away from me, all you who do evil.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CThere will be weeping and gnashing of teeth, for you will
        see Abraham, Isaac, Jacob, and all the prophets in the Kingdom of God, but
        you will be thrown out.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And people will come from all over the world\u2014from east and west,
        north and south\u2014to take their places in the Kingdom of God.  "
      comments: []
    - title: Jesus Grieves over Jerusalem
      content: "And note this: Some who seem least important now will be the greatest
        then, and some who are the greatest now will be least important then.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '13:30 '
        content: Greek <b>Some are last who will be first, and some are first who
          will be last.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "At that time some Pharisees said to him, \u201CGet away from here
        if you want to live! Herod Antipas wants to kill you!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Jesus replied, \u201CGo tell that fox that I will keep on casting
        out demons and healing people today and tomorrow; and the third day I will
        accomplish my purpose.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yes, today, tomorrow, and the next day I must proceed on my way.
        For it wouldn\u2019t do for a prophet of God to be killed except in Jerusalem!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CO Jerusalem, Jerusalem, the city that kills the prophets
        and stones God\u2019s messengers! How often I have wanted to gather your
        children together as a hen protects her chicks beneath her wings, but you
        wouldn\u2019t let me.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Jesus Heals on the Sabbath
      content: '  One Sabbath day Jesus went to eat dinner in the home of a leader
        of the Pharisees, and the people were watching him closely. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'There was a man there whose arms and legs were swollen.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '14:2 '
        content: Or <b>who had dropsy.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Jesus asked the Pharisees and experts in religious law, \u201CIs
        it permitted in the law to heal people on the Sabbath day, or not?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When they refused to answer, Jesus touched the sick man and healed
        him and sent him away. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then he turned to them and said, \u201CWhich of you doesn\u2019t
        work on the Sabbath? If your son[[COMMENT(0)]]  or your cow falls into a
        pit, don\u2019t you rush to get him out?\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '14:5 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>donkey.</b>
    - title: Jesus Teaches about Humility
      content: 'Again they could not answer.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When Jesus noticed that all who had come to the dinner were trying
        to sit in the seats of honor near the head of the table, he gave them this
        advice: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhen you are invited to a wedding feast, don\u2019t sit in
        the seat of honor. What if someone who is more distinguished than you has
        also been invited?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The host will come and say, \u2018Give this person your seat.\u2019
        Then you will be embarrassed, and you will have to take whatever seat is
        left at the foot of the table!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CInstead, take the lowest place at the foot of the table.
        Then when your host sees you, he will come and say, \u2018Friend, we have
        a better place for you!\u2019 Then you will be honored in front of all the
        other guests.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For those who exalt themselves will be humbled, and those who humble
        themselves will be exalted.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then he turned to his host. \u201CWhen you put on a luncheon or a
        banquet,\u201D he said, \u201Cdon\u2019t invite your friends, brothers, relatives,
        and rich neighbors. For they will invite you back, and that will be your
        only reward.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Instead, invite the poor, the crippled, the lame, and the blind.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Parable of the Great Feast
      content: "Then at the resurrection of the righteous, God will reward you for
        inviting those who could not repay you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Hearing this, a man sitting at the table with Jesus exclaimed, \u201CWhat
        a blessing it will be to attend a banquet[[COMMENT(0)]] in the Kingdom of
        God!\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '14:15 '
        content: Greek <b>to eat bread.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Jesus replied with this story: \u201CA man prepared a great feast
        and sent out many invitations.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When the banquet was ready, he sent his servant to tell the guests,
        \u2018Come, the banquet is ready.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But they all began making excuses. One said, \u2018I have just bought
        a field and must inspect it. Please excuse me.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Another said, \u2018I have just bought five pairs of oxen, and I
        want to try them out. Please excuse me.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Another said, \u2018I just got married, so I can\u2019t come.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CThe servant returned and told his master what they had said.
        His master was furious and said, \u2018Go quickly into the streets and alleys
        of the town and invite the poor, the crippled, the blind, and the lame.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "After the servant had done this, he reported, \u2018There is still
        room for more.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So his master said, \u2018Go out into the country lanes and behind
        the hedges and urge anyone you find to come, so that the house will be full.  "
      comments: []
    - title: The Cost of Being a Disciple
      content: "For none of those I first invited will get even the smallest taste
        of my banquet.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A large crowd was following Jesus. He turned around and said to them, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf you want to be my disciple, you must, by comparison, hate
        everyone else\u2014your father and mother, wife and children, brothers and
        sisters\u2014yes, even your own life. Otherwise, you cannot be my disciple.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And if you do not carry your own cross and follow me, you cannot
        be my disciple.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CBut don\u2019t begin until you count the cost. For who would
        begin construction of a building without first calculating the cost to see
        if there is enough money to finish it?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Otherwise, you might complete only the foundation before running
        out of money, and then everyone would laugh at you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They would say, \u2018There\u2019s the person who started that building
        and couldn\u2019t afford to finish it!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201COr what king would go to war against another king without
        first sitting down with his counselors to discuss whether his army of 10,000
        could defeat the 20,000 soldiers marching against him?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And if he can\u2019t, he will send a delegation to discuss terms
        of peace while the enemy is still far away.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So you cannot become my disciple without giving up everything you
        own.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CSalt is good for seasoning. But if it loses its flavor, how
        do you make it salty again?  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Parable of the Lost Sheep
      content: '  Tax collectors and other notorious sinners often came to listen
        to Jesus teach. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This made the Pharisees and teachers of religious law complain that
        he was associating with such sinful people\u2014even eating with them!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So Jesus told them this story: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf a man has a hundred sheep and one of them gets lost, what
        will he do? Won\u2019t he leave the ninety-nine others in the wilderness
        and go to search for the one that is lost until he finds it?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And when he has found it, he will joyfully carry it home on his shoulders.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When he arrives, he will call together his friends and neighbors,
        saying, \u2018Rejoice with me because I have found my lost sheep.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: Parable of the Lost Coin
      content: "In the same way, there is more joy in heaven over one lost sinner
        who repents and returns to God than over ninety-nine others who are righteous
        and haven\u2019t strayed away!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201COr suppose a woman has ten silver coins  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        and loses one. Won\u2019t she light a lamp and sweep the entire house and
        search carefully until she finds it?  "
      comments:
      - number: '15:8 '
        content: "  Greek   <b>ten drachmas. </b>  A drachma was the equivalent of
          a full day\u2019s wage.  "
    - title: 
      content: "And when she finds it, she will call in her friends and neighbors
        and say, \u2018Rejoice with me because I have found my lost coin.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: Parable of the Lost Son
      content: "In the same way, there is joy in the presence of God\u2019s angels
        when even one sinner repents.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "To illustrate the point further, Jesus told them this story: \u201CA
        man had two sons.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The younger son told his father, \u2018I want my share of your estate
        now before you die.\u2019 So his father agreed to divide his wealth between
        his sons.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CA few days later this younger son packed all his belongings
        and moved to a distant land, and there he wasted all his money in wild living.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'About the time his money ran out, a great famine swept over the land,
        and he began to starve.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He persuaded a local farmer to hire him, and the man sent him into
        his fields to feed the pigs.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The young man became so hungry that even the pods he was feeding
        the pigs looked good to him. But no one gave him anything.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CWhen he finally came to his senses, he said to himself, \u2018At
        home even the hired servants have food enough to spare, and here I am dying
        of hunger!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I will go home to my father and say, \u201CFather, I have sinned
        against both heaven and you,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "and I am no longer worthy of being called your son. Please take me
        on as a hired servant.\u201D\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CSo he returned home to his father. And while he was still
        a long way off, his father saw him coming. Filled with love and compassion,
        he ran to his son, embraced him, and kissed him.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "His son said to him, \u2018Father, I have sinned against both heaven
        and you, and I am no longer worthy of being called your son.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '15:21 '
        content: Some manuscripts add <b>Please take me on as a hired servant.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CBut his father said to the servants, \u2018Quick! Bring the
        finest robe in the house and put it on him. Get a ring for his finger and
        sandals for his feet.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And kill the calf we have been fattening. We must celebrate with
        a feast,  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "for this son of mine was dead and has now returned to life. He was
        lost, but now he is found.\u2019 So the party began.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CMeanwhile, the older son was in the fields working. When
        he returned home, he heard music and dancing in the house,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and he asked one of the servants what was going on.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u2018Your brother is back,\u2019 he was told, \u2018and your father
        has killed the fattened calf. We are celebrating because of his safe return.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CThe older brother was angry and wouldn\u2019t go in. His
        father came out and begged him,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "but he replied, \u2018All these years I\u2019ve slaved for you and
        never once refused to do a single thing you told me to. And in all that time
        you never gave me even one young goat for a feast with my friends.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yet when this son of yours comes back after squandering your money
        on prostitutes, you celebrate by killing the fattened calf!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CHis father said to him, \u2018Look, dear son, you have always
        stayed by me, and everything I have is yours.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Parable of the Shrewd Manager
      content: "  Jesus told this story to his disciples: \u201CThere was a certain
        rich man who had a manager handling his affairs. One day a report came that
        the manager was wasting his employer\u2019s money.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So the employer called him in and said, \u2018What\u2019s this I
        hear about you? Get your report in order, because you are going to be fired.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CThe manager thought to himself, \u2018Now what? My boss has
        fired me. I don\u2019t have the strength to dig ditches, and I\u2019m too
        proud to beg.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Ah, I know how to ensure that I\u2019ll have plenty of friends who
        will give me a home when I am fired.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CSo he invited each person who owed money to his employer
        to come and discuss the situation. He asked the first one, \u2018How much
        do you owe him?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The man replied, \u2018I owe him 800 gallons of olive oil.\u2019
        So the manager told him, \u2018Take the bill and quickly change it to 400
        gallons.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '16:6 '
        content: 'Greek <b>100 baths . . . 50 [baths].</b>  '
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201C\u2018And how much do you owe my employer?\u2019 he asked
        the next man. \u2018I owe him 1,000 bushels of wheat,\u2019 was the reply.
        \u2018Here,\u2019 the manager said, \u2018take the bill and change it to
        800 bushels.  [[COMMENT(0)]]  \u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '16:7 '
        content: '  Greek   <b>100 korous . . . 80 [korous].</b>  '
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CThe rich man had to admire the dishonest rascal for being
        so shrewd. And it is true that the children of this world are more shrewd
        in dealing with the world around them than are the children of the light.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Here\u2019s the lesson: Use your worldly resources to benefit others
        and make friends. Then, when your possessions are gone, they will welcome
        you to an eternal home.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '16:9 '
        content: 'Or <b>you will be welcomed into eternal homes.</b>  '
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CIf you are faithful in little things, you will be faithful
        in large ones. But if you are dishonest in little things, you won\u2019t
        be honest with greater responsibilities.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And if you are untrustworthy about worldly wealth, who will trust
        you with the true riches of heaven?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And if you are not faithful with other people\u2019s things, why
        should you be trusted with things of your own?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CNo one can serve two masters. For you will hate one and love
        the other; you will be devoted to one and despise the other. You cannot serve
        God and be enslaved to money.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The Pharisees, who dearly loved their money, heard all this and scoffed
        at him. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then he said to them, \u201CYou like to appear righteous in public,
        but God knows your hearts. What this world honors is detestable in the sight
        of God.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CUntil John the Baptist, the law of Moses and the messages
        of the prophets were your guides. But now the Good News of the Kingdom of
        God is preached, and everyone is eager to get in.  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '16:16 '
        content: '  Or   <b>everyone is urged to enter in.</b>    '
    - title: 
      content: "But that doesn\u2019t mean that the law has lost its force. It is
        easier for heaven and earth to disappear than for the smallest point of God\u2019s
        law to be overturned.  "
      comments: []
    - title: Parable of the Rich Man and Lazarus
      content: "  \u201CFor example, a man who divorces his wife and marries someone
        else commits adultery. And anyone who marries a woman divorced from her husband
        commits adultery.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Jesus said, \u201CThere was a certain rich man who was splendidly
        clothed in purple and fine linen and who lived each day in luxury.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'At his gate lay a poor man named Lazarus who was covered with sores.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As Lazarus lay there longing for scraps from the rich man\u2019s
        table, the dogs would come and lick his open sores.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CFinally, the poor man died and was carried by the angels
        to sit beside Abraham at the heavenly banquet.  [[COMMENT(0)]]  The rich
        man also died and was buried,  "
      comments:
      - number: '16:22 '
        content: "  Greek   <b>to Abraham\u2019s bosom.</b>  "
    - title: 
      content: 'and he went to the place of the dead.[[COMMENT(0)]]  There, in torment,
        he saw Abraham in the far distance with Lazarus at his side.  '
      comments:
      - number: '16:23 '
        content: Greek <b>to Hades.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CThe rich man shouted, \u2018Father Abraham, have some pity!
        Send Lazarus over here to dip the tip of his finger in water and cool my
        tongue. I am in anguish in these flames.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CBut Abraham said to him, \u2018Son, remember that during
        your lifetime you had everything you wanted, and Lazarus had nothing. So
        now he is here being comforted, and you are in anguish.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And besides, there is a great chasm separating us. No one can cross
        over to you from here, and no one can cross over to us from there.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CThen the rich man said, \u2018Please, Father Abraham, at
        least send him to my father\u2019s home.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For I have five brothers, and I want him to warn them so they don\u2019t
        end up in this place of torment.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CBut Abraham said, \u2018Moses and the prophets have warned
        them. Your brothers can read what they wrote.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CThe rich man replied, \u2018No, Father Abraham! But if someone
        is sent to them from the dead, then they will repent of their sins and turn
        to God.\u2019  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Teachings about Forgiveness and Faith
      content: "  One day Jesus said to his disciples, \u201CThere will always be
        temptations to sin, but what sorrow awaits the person who does the tempting!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It would be better to be thrown into the sea with a millstone hung
        around your neck than to cause one of these little ones to fall into sin.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So watch yourselves!  \u201CIf another believer  [[COMMENT(0)]] 
        sins, rebuke that person; then if there is repentance, forgive.  "
      comments:
      - number: '17:3 '
        content: '  Greek   <b>If your brother.</b>  '
    - title: 
      content: "Even if that person wrongs you seven times a day and each time turns
        again and asks forgiveness, you must forgive.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The apostles said to the Lord, \u201CShow us how to increase our
        faith.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The Lord answered, \u201CIf you had faith even as small as a mustard
        seed, you could say to this mulberry tree, \u2018May you be uprooted and
        be planted in the sea,\u2019 and it would obey you!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CWhen a servant comes in from plowing or taking care of sheep,
        does his master say, \u2018Come in and eat with me\u2019?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "No, he says, \u2018Prepare my meal, put on your apron, and serve
        me while I eat. Then you can eat later.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And does the master thank the servant for doing what he was told
        to do? Of course not.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Ten Healed of Leprosy
      content: "In the same way, when you obey me you should say, \u2018We are unworthy
        servants who have simply done our duty.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As Jesus continued on toward Jerusalem, he reached the border between
        Galilee and Samaria. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As he entered a village there, ten men with leprosy stood at a distance, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "crying out, \u201CJesus, Master, have mercy on us!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He looked at them and said, \u201CGo show yourselves to the priests.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]
        And as they went, they were cleansed of their leprosy.  "
      comments:
      - number: '17:14 '
        content: See Lev 14:2-32.
    - title: 
      content: "One of them, when he saw that he was healed, came back to Jesus,
        shouting, \u201CPraise God!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He fell to the ground at Jesus\u2019 feet, thanking him for what
        he had done. This man was a Samaritan.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Jesus asked, \u201CDidn\u2019t I heal ten men? Where are the other
        nine?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Has no one returned to give glory to God except this foreigner?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: The Coming of the Kingdom
      content: "And Jesus said to the man, \u201CStand up and go. Your faith has
        healed you.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '17:19 '
        content: Or <b>Your faith has saved you.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "One day the Pharisees asked Jesus, \u201CWhen will the Kingdom of
        God come?\u201DJesus replied, \u201CThe Kingdom of God can\u2019t be detected
        by visible signs.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '17:20 '
        content: Or <b>by your speculations.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "You won\u2019t be able to say, \u2018Here it is!\u2019 or \u2018It\u2019s
        over there!\u2019 For the Kingdom of God is already among you.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '17:21 '
        content: Or <b>is within you, </b>or <b>is in your grasp.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Then he said to his disciples, \u201CThe time is coming when you
        will long to see the day when the Son of Man returns,[[COMMENT(0)]]  but
        you won\u2019t see it.  "
      comments:
      - number: '17:22 '
        content: "Or <b>long for even one day with the Son of Man. </b>\u201CSon
          of Man\u201D is a title Jesus used for himself."
    - title: 
      content: "People will tell you, \u2018Look, there is the Son of Man,\u2019
        or \u2018Here he is,\u2019 but don\u2019t go out and follow them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For as the lightning flashes and lights up the sky from one end to
        the other, so it will be on the day[[COMMENT(0)]]  when the Son of Man comes.  '
      comments:
      - number: '17:24 '
        content: Some manuscripts do not include <b>on the day.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'But first the Son of Man must suffer terribly[[COMMENT(0)]]  and
        be rejected by this generation.  '
      comments:
      - number: '17:25 '
        content: Or <b>suffer many things.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CWhen the Son of Man returns, it will be like it was in Noah\u2019s
        day.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In those days, the people enjoyed banquets and parties and weddings
        right up to the time Noah entered his boat and the flood came and destroyed
        them all.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CAnd the world will be as it was in the days of Lot. People
        went about their daily business\u2014eating and drinking, buying and selling,
        farming and building\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'until the morning Lot left Sodom. Then fire and burning sulfur rained
        down from heaven and destroyed them all.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yes, it will be \u2018business as usual\u2019 right up to the day
        when the Son of Man is revealed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'On that day a person out on the deck of a roof must not go down into
        the house to pack. A person out in the field must not return home.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Remember what happened to Lot\u2019s wife!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If you cling to your life, you will lose it, and if you let your
        life go, you will save it.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'That night two people will be asleep in one bed; one will be taken,
        the other left.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Two women will be grinding flour together at the mill; one will be
        taken, the other left.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '17:35 '
        content: Some manuscripts add verse 36, <b>Two men will be working in the
          field; one will be taken, the other left. </b>Compare Matt 24:40.
  - verses:
    - title: Parable of the Persistent Widow
      content: '  One day Jesus told his disciples a story to show that they should
        always pray and never give up. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThere was a judge in a certain city,\u201D he said, \u201Cwho
        neither feared God nor cared about people.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A widow of that city came to him repeatedly, saying, \u2018Give me
        justice in this dispute with my enemy.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The judge ignored her for a while, but finally he said to himself,
        \u2018I don\u2019t fear God or care about people,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "but this woman is driving me crazy. I\u2019m going to see that she
        gets justice, because she is wearing me out with her constant requests!\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the Lord said, \u201CLearn a lesson from this unjust judge.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Even he rendered a just decision in the end. So don\u2019t you think
        God will surely give justice to his chosen people who cry out to him day
        and night? Will he keep putting them off?  "
      comments: []
    - title: Parable of the Pharisee and Tax Collector
      content: "I tell you, he will grant justice to them quickly! But when the Son
        of Man[[COMMENT(0)]]  returns, how many will he find on the earth who have
        faith?\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '18:8 '
        content: "\u201CSon of Man\u201D is a title Jesus used for himself."
    - title: 
      content: 'Then Jesus told this story to some who had great confidence in their
        own righteousness and scorned everyone else: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTwo men went to the Temple to pray. One was a Pharisee, and
        the other was a despised tax collector.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The Pharisee stood by himself and prayed this prayer[[COMMENT(0)]]:
        \u2018I thank you, God, that I am not like other people\u2014cheaters, sinners,
        adulterers. I\u2019m certainly not like that tax collector!  "
      comments:
      - number: '18:11 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>stood and prayed this prayer to himself.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "I fast twice a week, and I give you a tenth of my income.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CBut the tax collector stood at a distance and dared not even
        lift his eyes to heaven as he prayed. Instead, he beat his chest in sorrow,
        saying, \u2018O God, be merciful to me, for I am a sinner.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: Jesus Blesses the Children
      content: "I tell you, this sinner, not the Pharisee, returned home justified
        before God. For those who exalt themselves will be humbled, and those who
        humble themselves will be exalted.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'One day some parents brought their little children to Jesus so he
        could touch and bless them. But when the disciples saw this, they scolded
        the parents for bothering him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Jesus called for the children and said to the disciples, \u201CLet
        the children come to me. Don\u2019t stop them! For the Kingdom of God belongs
        to those who are like these children.  "
      comments: []
    - title: The Rich Man
      content: "I tell you the truth, anyone who doesn\u2019t receive the Kingdom
        of God like a child will never enter it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Once a religious leader asked Jesus this question: \u201CGood Teacher,
        what should I do to inherit eternal life?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CWhy do you call me good?\u201D Jesus asked him. \u201COnly
        God is truly good.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But to answer your question, you know the commandments: \u2018You
        must not commit adultery. You must not murder. You must not steal. You must
        not testify falsely. Honor your father and mother.\u2019[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '18:20 '
        content: Exod 20:12-16; Deut 5:16-20.
    - title: 
      content: "The man replied, \u201CI\u2019ve obeyed all these commandments since
        I was young.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When Jesus heard his answer, he said, \u201CThere is still one thing
        you haven\u2019t done. Sell all your possessions and give the money to the
        poor, and you will have treasure in heaven. Then come, follow me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But when the man heard this he became very sad, for he was very rich.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When Jesus saw this,[[COMMENT(0)]] he said, \u201CHow hard it is
        for the rich to enter the Kingdom of God!  "
      comments:
      - number: '18:24 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>When Jesus saw how sad the man was.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "In fact, it is easier for a camel to go through the eye of a needle
        than for a rich person to enter the Kingdom of God!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Those who heard this said, \u201CThen who in the world can be saved?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He replied, \u201CWhat is impossible for people is possible with
        God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Peter said, \u201CWe\u2019ve left our homes to follow you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CYes,\u201D Jesus replied, \u201Cand I assure you that everyone
        who has given up house or wife or brothers or parents or children, for the
        sake of the Kingdom of God,  "
      comments: []
    - title: Jesus Again Predicts His Death
      content: "will be repaid many times over in this life, and will have eternal
        life in the world to come.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Taking the twelve disciples aside, Jesus said, \u201CListen, we\u2019re
        going up to Jerusalem, where all the predictions of the prophets concerning
        the Son of Man will come true.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He will be handed over to the Romans,[[COMMENT(0)]]  and he will
        be mocked, treated shamefully, and spit upon.  '
      comments:
      - number: '18:32 '
        content: Greek <b>the Gentiles.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "They will flog him with a whip and kill him, but on the third day
        he will rise again.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Jesus Heals a Blind Beggar
      content: "But they didn\u2019t understand any of this. The significance of
        his words was hidden from them, and they failed to grasp what he was talking
        about.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As Jesus approached Jericho, a blind beggar was sitting beside the
        road. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When he heard the noise of a crowd going past, he asked what was
        happening. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They told him that Jesus the Nazarene[[COMMENT(0)]] was going by. '
      comments:
      - number: '18:37 '
        content: Or <b>Jesus of Nazareth.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "So he began shouting, \u201CJesus, Son of David, have mercy on me!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBe quiet!\u201D the people in front yelled at him.But he only
        shouted louder, \u201CSon of David, have mercy on me!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When Jesus heard him, he stopped and ordered that the man be brought
        to him. As the man came near, Jesus asked him, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhat do you want me to do for you?\u201D\u201CLord,\u201D he
        said, \u201CI want to see!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And Jesus said, \u201CAll right, receive your sight! Your faith has
        healed you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Jesus and Zacchaeus
      content: '  Jesus entered Jericho and made his way through the town. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'There was a man there named Zacchaeus. He was the chief tax collector
        in the region, and he had become very rich. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He tried to get a look at Jesus, but he was too short to see over
        the crowd. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So he ran ahead and climbed a sycamore-fig tree beside the road,
        for Jesus was going to pass that way.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When Jesus came by, he looked up at Zacchaeus and called him by name.
        \u201CZacchaeus!\u201D he said. \u201CQuick, come down! I must be a guest
        in your home today.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Zacchaeus quickly climbed down and took Jesus to his house in great
        excitement and joy. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But the people were displeased. \u201CHe has gone to be the guest
        of a notorious sinner,\u201D they grumbled.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Meanwhile, Zacchaeus stood before the Lord and said, \u201CI will
        give half my wealth to the poor, Lord, and if I have cheated people on their
        taxes, I will give them back four times as much!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Jesus responded, \u201CSalvation has come to this home today, for
        this man has shown himself to be a true son of Abraham.  "
      comments: []
    - title: Parable of the Ten Servants
      content: "For the Son of Man[[COMMENT(0)]]  came to seek and save those who
        are lost.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '19:10 '
        content: "\u201CSon of Man\u201D is a title Jesus used for himself."
    - title: 
      content: 'The crowd was listening to everything Jesus said. And because he
        was nearing Jerusalem, he told them a story to correct the impression that
        the Kingdom of God would begin right away. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He said, \u201CA nobleman was called away to a distant empire to
        be crowned king and then return.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Before he left, he called together ten of his servants and divided
        among them ten pounds of silver,[[COMMENT(0)]]  saying, \u2018Invest this
        for me while I am gone.\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '19:13 '
        content: "Greek <b>ten minas; </b>one mina was worth about three months\u2019
          wages."
    - title: 
      content: "But his people hated him and sent a delegation after him to say,
        \u2018We do not want him to be our king.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CAfter he was crowned king, he returned and called in the
        servants to whom he had given the money. He wanted to find out what their
        profits were.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The first servant reported, \u2018Master, I invested your money and
        made ten times the original amount!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201C\u2018Well done!\u2019 the king exclaimed. \u2018You are
        a good servant. You have been faithful with the little I entrusted to you,
        so you will be governor of ten cities as your reward.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CThe next servant reported, \u2018Master, I invested your
        money and made five times the original amount.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201C\u2018Well done!\u2019 the king said. \u2018You will be governor
        over five cities.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CBut the third servant brought back only the original amount
        of money and said, \u2018Master, I hid your money and kept it safe.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I was afraid because you are a hard man to deal with, taking what
        isn\u2019t yours and harvesting crops you didn\u2019t plant.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201C\u2018You wicked servant!\u2019 the king roared. \u2018Your
        own words condemn you. If you knew that I\u2019m a hard man who takes what
        isn\u2019t mine and harvests crops I didn\u2019t plant,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "why didn\u2019t you deposit my money in the bank? At least I could
        have gotten some interest on it.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CThen, turning to the others standing nearby, the king ordered,
        \u2018Take the money from this servant, and give it to the one who has ten
        pounds.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201C\u2018But, master,\u2019 they said, \u2018he already has
        ten pounds!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201C\u2018Yes,\u2019 the king replied, \u2018and to those who
        use well what they are given, even more will be given. But from those who
        do nothing, even what little they have will be taken away.  "
      comments: []
    - title: "Jesus\u2019 Triumphant Entry"
      content: "And as for these enemies of mine who didn\u2019t want me to be their
        king\u2014bring them in and execute them right here in front of me.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'After telling this story, Jesus went on toward Jerusalem, walking
        ahead of his disciples. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As he came to the towns of Bethphage and Bethany on the Mount of
        Olives, he sent two disciples ahead. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGo into that village over there,\u201D he told them. \u201CAs
        you enter it, you will see a young donkey tied there that no one has ever
        ridden. Untie it and bring it here.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If anyone asks, \u2018Why are you untying that colt?\u2019 just say,
        \u2018The Lord needs it.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So they went and found the colt, just as Jesus had said. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And sure enough, as they were untying it, the owners asked them,
        \u201CWhy are you untying that colt?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And the disciples simply replied, \u201CThe Lord needs it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So they brought the colt to Jesus and threw their garments over it
        for him to ride on.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As he rode along, the crowds spread out their garments on the road
        ahead of him. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When he reached the place where the road started down the Mount of
        Olives, all of his followers began to shout and sing as they walked along,
        praising God for all the wonderful miracles they had seen.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBlessings on the King who comes in the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>!Peace
        in heaven, and glory in highest heaven!\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '19:38 '
        content: Pss 118:26; 148:1.
    - title: 
      content: "But some of the Pharisees among the crowd said, \u201CTeacher, rebuke
        your followers for saying things like that!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Jesus Weeps over Jerusalem
      content: "He replied, \u201CIf they kept quiet, the stones along the road would
        burst into cheers!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But as he came closer to Jerusalem and saw the city ahead, he began
        to weep. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CHow I wish today that you of all people would understand the
        way to peace. But now it is too late, and peace is hidden from your eyes.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Before long your enemies will build ramparts against your walls and
        encircle you and close in on you from every side.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Jesus Clears the Temple
      content: "They will crush you into the ground, and your children with you.
        Your enemies will not leave a single stone in place, because you did not
        recognize it when God visited you.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '19:44 '
        content: "Greek <b>did not recognize the time of your visitation, </b>a reference
          to the Messiah\u2019s coming."
    - title: 
      content: 'Then Jesus entered the Temple and began to drive out the people selling
        animals for sacrifices. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He said to them, \u201CThe Scriptures declare, \u2018My Temple will
        be a house of prayer,\u2019 but you have turned it into a den of thieves.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '19:46 '
        content: Isa 56:7; Jer 7:11.
    - title: 
      content: 'After that, he taught daily in the Temple, but the leading priests,
        the teachers of religious law, and the other leaders of the people began
        planning how to kill him. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Authority of Jesus Challenged
      content: '  One day as Jesus was teaching the people and preaching the Good
        News in the Temple, the leading priests, the teachers of religious law, and
        the elders came up to him. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They demanded, \u201CBy what authority are you doing all these things?
        Who gave you the right?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CLet me ask you a question first,\u201D he replied. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CDid John\u2019s authority to baptize come from heaven, or was
        it merely human?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They talked it over among themselves. \u201CIf we say it was from
        heaven, he will ask why we didn\u2019t believe John. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But if we say it was merely human, the people will stone us because
        they are convinced John was a prophet.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So they finally replied that they didn\u2019t know.  "
      comments: []
    - title: Parable of the Evil Farmers
      content: "And Jesus responded, \u201CThen I won\u2019t tell you by what authority
        I do these things.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Now Jesus turned to the people again and told them this story: \u201CA
        man planted a vineyard, leased it to tenant farmers, and moved to another
        country to live for several years.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'At the time of the grape harvest, he sent one of his servants to
        collect his share of the crop. But the farmers attacked the servant, beat
        him up, and sent him back empty-handed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So the owner sent another servant, but they also insulted him, beat
        him up, and sent him away empty-handed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'A third man was sent, and they wounded him and chased him away.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201C\u2018What will I do?\u2019 the owner asked himself. \u2018I
        know! I\u2019ll send my cherished son. Surely they will respect him.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CBut when the tenant farmers saw his son, they said to each
        other, \u2018Here comes the heir to this estate. Let\u2019s kill him and
        get the estate for ourselves!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So they dragged him out of the vineyard and murdered him.  \u201CWhat
        do you suppose the owner of the vineyard will do to them?\u201D Jesus asked. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI\u2019ll tell you\u2014he will come and kill those farmers
        and lease the vineyard to others.\u201D\u201CHow terrible that such a thing
        should ever happen,\u201D his listeners protested.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Jesus looked at them and said, \u201CThen what does this Scripture
        mean?  \u2018The stone that the builders rejected  has now become the cornerstone.\u2019 
        [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '20:17 '
        content: '  Ps 118:22.  '
    - title: 
      content: "  Everyone who stumbles over that stone will be broken to pieces,
        and it will crush anyone it falls on.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Taxes for Caesar
      content: "The teachers of religious law and the leading priests wanted to arrest
        Jesus immediately because they realized he was telling the story against
        them\u2014they were the wicked farmers. But they were afraid of the people\u2019s
        reaction.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Watching for their opportunity, the leaders sent spies pretending
        to be honest men. They tried to get Jesus to say something that could be
        reported to the Roman governor so he would arrest Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTeacher,\u201D they said, \u201Cwe know that you speak and
        teach what is right and are not influenced by what others think. You teach
        the way of God truthfully. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Now tell us\u2014is it right for us to pay taxes to Caesar or not?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He saw through their trickery and said, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CShow me a Roman coin.[[COMMENT(0)]]  Whose picture and title
        are stamped on it?\u201D\u201CCaesar\u2019s,\u201D they replied.  "
      comments:
      - number: '20:24 '
        content: Greek <b>a denarius.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CWell then,\u201D he said, \u201Cgive to Caesar what belongs
        to Caesar, and give to God what belongs to God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: Discussion about Resurrection
      content: 'So they failed to trap him by what he said in front of the people.
        Instead, they were amazed by his answer, and they became silent.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Jesus was approached by some Sadducees\u2014religious leaders
        who say there is no resurrection from the dead. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They posed this question: \u201CTeacher, Moses gave us a law that
        if a man dies, leaving a wife but no children, his brother should marry the
        widow and have a child who will carry on the brother\u2019s name.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '20:28 '
        content: 'See Deut 25:5-6.  '
    - title: 
      content: 'Well, suppose there were seven brothers. The oldest one married and
        then died without children. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So the second brother married the widow, but he also died. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the third brother married her. This continued with all seven
        of them, who died without children. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Finally, the woman also died. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So tell us, whose wife will she be in the resurrection? For all seven
        were married to her!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Jesus replied, \u201CMarriage is for people here on earth.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But in the age to come, those worthy of being raised from the dead
        will neither marry nor be given in marriage.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And they will never die again. In this respect they will be like
        angels. They are children of God and children of the resurrection.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CBut now, as to whether the dead will be raised\u2014even
        Moses proved this when he wrote about the burning bush. Long after Abraham,
        Isaac, and Jacob had died, he referred to the Lord  [[COMMENT(0)]]  as \u2018the
        God of Abraham, the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob.\u2019[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '20:37a '
        content: '  Greek   <b>when he wrote about the bush. He referred to the Lord.</b>  '
      - number: '20:37b '
        content: 'Exod 3:6.  '
    - title: 
      content: "So he is the God of the living, not the dead, for they are all alive
        to him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWell said, Teacher!\u201D remarked some of the teachers of
        religious law who were standing there. "
      comments: []
    - title: Whose Son Is the Messiah?
      content: 'And then no one dared to ask him any more questions.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Jesus presented them with a question. \u201CWhy is it,\u201D
        he asked, \u201Cthat the Messiah is said to be the son of David?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For David himself wrote in the book of Psalms:  \u2018The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        said to my Lord,  Sit in the place of honor at my right hand  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  until I humble your enemies,  making them a footstool under your
        feet.\u2019  [[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '20:42-43 '
        content: '  Ps 110:1.  '
    - title: 
      content: "  Since David called the Messiah \u2018Lord,\u2019 how can the Messiah
        be his son?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then, with the crowds listening, he turned to his disciples and said, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBeware of these teachers of religious law! For they like to
        parade around in flowing robes and love to receive respectful greetings as
        they walk in the marketplaces. And how they love the seats of honor in the
        synagogues and the head table at banquets.  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "The Widow\u2019s Offering"
      content: '  While Jesus was in the Temple, he watched the rich people dropping
        their gifts in the collection box. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then a poor widow came by and dropped in two small coins.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '21:2 '
        content: Greek <b>two lepta </b>[the smallest of Jewish coins].
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CI tell you the truth,\u201D Jesus said, \u201Cthis poor widow
        has given more than all the rest of them.  "
      comments: []
    - title: Jesus Speaks about the Future
      content: "For they have given a tiny part of their surplus, but she, poor as
        she is, has given everything she has.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Some of his disciples began talking about the majestic stonework
        of the Temple and the memorial decorations on the walls. But Jesus said, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe time is coming when all these things will be completely
        demolished. Not one stone will be left on top of another!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CTeacher,\u201D they asked, \u201Cwhen will all this happen?
        What sign will show us that these things are about to take place?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He replied, \u201CDon\u2019t let anyone mislead you, for many will
        come in my name, claiming, \u2018I am the Messiah,\u2019[[COMMENT(0)]]  and
        saying, \u2018The time has come!\u2019 But don\u2019t believe them.  "
      comments:
      - number: '21:8 '
        content: "Greek <b>claiming, \u2018I am.\u2019</b>"
    - title: 
      content: "And when you hear of wars and insurrections, don\u2019t panic. Yes,
        these things must take place first, but the end won\u2019t follow immediately.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then he added, \u201CNation will go to war against nation, and kingdom
        against kingdom.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'There will be great earthquakes, and there will be famines and plagues
        in many lands, and there will be terrifying things and great miraculous signs
        from heaven.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CBut before all this occurs, there will be a time of great
        persecution. You will be dragged into synagogues and prisons, and you will
        stand trial before kings and governors because you are my followers.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But this will be your opportunity to tell them about me.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '21:13 '
        content: Or <b>This will be your testimony against them.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "So don\u2019t worry in advance about how to answer the charges against
        you,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'for I will give you the right words and such wisdom that none of
        your opponents will be able to reply or refute you!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Even those closest to you\u2014your parents, brothers, relatives,
        and friends\u2014will betray you. They will even kill some of you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And everyone will hate you because you are my followers.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '21:17 '
        content: Greek <b>on account of my name.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'But not a hair of your head will perish!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'By standing firm, you will win your souls.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CAnd when you see Jerusalem surrounded by armies, then you
        will know that the time of its destruction has arrived.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then those in Judea must flee to the hills. Those in Jerusalem must
        get out, and those out in the country should not return to the city.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For those will be days of God\u2019s vengeance, and the prophetic
        words of the Scriptures will be fulfilled.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'How terrible it will be for pregnant women and for nursing mothers
        in those days. For there will be disaster in the land and great anger against
        this people.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They will be killed by the sword or sent away as captives to all
        the nations of the world. And Jerusalem will be trampled down by the Gentiles
        until the period of the Gentiles comes to an end.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CAnd there will be strange signs in the sun, moon, and stars.
        And here on earth the nations will be in turmoil, perplexed by the roaring
        seas and strange tides.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'People will be terrified at what they see coming upon the earth,
        for the powers in the heavens will be shaken.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then everyone will see the Son of Man[[COMMENT(0)]]  coming on a
        cloud with power and great glory.[[COMMENT(1)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '21:27a '
        content: "\u201CSon of Man\u201D is a title Jesus used for himself."
      - number: '21:27b '
        content: See Dan 7:13.
    - title: 
      content: "So when all these things begin to happen, stand and look up, for
        your salvation is near!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then he gave them this illustration: \u201CNotice the fig tree, or
        any other tree.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When the leaves come out, you know without being told that summer
        is near.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In the same way, when you see all these things taking place, you
        can know that the Kingdom of God is near.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I tell you the truth, this generation will not pass from the scene
        until all these things have taken place.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Heaven and earth will disappear, but my words will never disappear.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CWatch out! Don\u2019t let your hearts be dulled by carousing
        and drunkenness, and by the worries of this life. Don\u2019t let that day
        catch you unaware,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'like a trap. For that day will come upon everyone living on the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Keep alert at all times. And pray that you might be strong enough
        to escape these coming horrors and stand before the Son of Man.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Every day Jesus went to the Temple to teach, and each evening he
        returned to spend the night on the Mount of Olives. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Judas Agrees to Betray Jesus
      content: '  The Festival of Unleavened Bread, which is also called Passover,
        was approaching. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The leading priests and teachers of religious law were plotting how
        to kill Jesus, but they were afraid of the people\u2019s reaction.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then Satan entered into Judas Iscariot, who was one of the twelve
        disciples, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and he went to the leading priests and captains of the Temple guard
        to discuss the best way to betray Jesus to them. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They were delighted, and they promised to give him money. '
      comments: []
    - title: The Last Supper
      content: "So he agreed and began looking for an opportunity to betray Jesus
        so they could arrest him when the crowds weren\u2019t around.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Now the Festival of Unleavened Bread arrived, when the Passover lamb
        is sacrificed. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Jesus sent Peter and John ahead and said, \u201CGo and prepare the
        Passover meal, so we can eat it together.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhere do you want us to prepare it?\u201D they asked him.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He replied, \u201CAs soon as you enter Jerusalem, a man carrying
        a pitcher of water will meet you. Follow him. At the house he enters,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "say to the owner, \u2018The Teacher asks: Where is the guest room
        where I can eat the Passover meal with my disciples?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He will take you upstairs to a large room that is already set up.
        That is where you should prepare our meal.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They went off to the city and found everything just as Jesus had
        said, and they prepared the Passover meal there.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When the time came, Jesus and the apostles sat down together at the
        table.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '22:14 '
        content: Or <b>reclined together.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Jesus said, \u201CI have been very eager to eat this Passover meal
        with you before my suffering begins.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For I tell you now that I won\u2019t eat this meal again until its
        meaning is fulfilled in the Kingdom of God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then he took a cup of wine and gave thanks to God for it. Then he
        said, \u201CTake this and share it among yourselves.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For I will not drink wine again until the Kingdom of God has come.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He took some bread and gave thanks to God for it. Then he broke it
        in pieces and gave it to the disciples, saying, \u201CThis is my body, which
        is given for you. Do this in remembrance of me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "After supper he took another cup of wine and said, \u201CThis cup
        is the new covenant between God and his people\u2014an agreement confirmed
        with my blood, which is poured out as a sacrifice for you.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '22:19-20 '
        content: Some manuscripts do not include 22:19b-20, <b>which is given for
          you . . . which is poured out as a sacrifice for you.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CBut here at this table, sitting among us as a friend, is
        the man who will betray me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For it has been determined that the Son of Man[[COMMENT(0)]]  must
        die. But what sorrow awaits the one who betrays him.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '22:22 '
        content: "\u201CSon of Man\u201D is a title Jesus used for himself."
    - title: 
      content: 'The disciples began to ask each other which of them would ever do
        such a thing.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then they began to argue among themselves about who would be the
        greatest among them. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Jesus told them, \u201CIn this world the kings and great men lord
        it over their people, yet they are called \u2018friends of the people.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But among you it will be different. Those who are the greatest among
        you should take the lowest rank, and the leader should be like a servant.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Who is more important, the one who sits at the table or the one who
        serves? The one who sits at the table, of course. But not here! For I am
        among you as one who serves.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CYou have stayed with me in my time of trial.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And just as my Father has granted me a Kingdom, I now grant you the
        right  '
      comments: []
    - title: "Jesus Predicts Peter\u2019s Denial"
      content: 'to eat and drink at my table in my Kingdom. And you will sit on thrones,
        judging the twelve tribes of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CSimon, Simon, Satan has asked to sift each of you like wheat.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But I have pleaded in prayer for you, Simon, that your faith should
        not fail. So when you have repented and turned to me again, strengthen your
        brothers.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Peter said, \u201CLord, I am ready to go to prison with you, and
        even to die with you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But Jesus said, \u201CPeter, let me tell you something. Before the
        rooster crows tomorrow morning, you will deny three times that you even know
        me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Jesus asked them, \u201CWhen I sent you out to preach the Good
        News and you did not have money, a traveler\u2019s bag, or an extra pair
        of sandals, did you need anything?\u201D\u201CNo,\u201D they replied.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CBut now,\u201D he said, \u201Ctake your money and a traveler\u2019s
        bag. And if you don\u2019t have a sword, sell your cloak and buy one!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the time has come for this prophecy about me to be fulfilled:
        \u2018He was counted among the rebels.\u2019[[COMMENT(0)]]  Yes, everything
        written about me by the prophets will come true.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '22:37 '
        content: Isa 53:12.
    - title: Jesus Prays on the Mount of Olives
      content: "\u201CLook, Lord,\u201D they replied, \u201Cwe have two swords among
        us.\u201D  \u201CThat\u2019s enough,\u201D he said.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then, accompanied by the disciples, Jesus left the upstairs room
        and went as usual to the Mount of Olives. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "There he told them, \u201CPray that you will not give in to temptation.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He walked away, about a stone\u2019s throw, and knelt down and prayed, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CFather, if you are willing, please take this cup of suffering
        away from me. Yet I want your will to be done, not mine.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then an angel from heaven appeared and strengthened him. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He prayed more fervently, and he was in such agony of spirit that
        his sweat fell to the ground like great drops of blood.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '22:43-44 '
        content: Verses 43 and 44 are not included in the most ancient manuscripts.
    - title: 
      content: 'At last he stood up again and returned to the disciples, only to
        find them asleep, exhausted from grief. '
      comments: []
    - title: Jesus Is Betrayed and Arrested
      content: "\u201CWhy are you sleeping?\u201D he asked them. \u201CGet up and
        pray, so that you will not give in to temptation.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But even as Jesus said this, a crowd approached, led by Judas, one
        of the twelve disciples. Judas walked over to Jesus to greet him with a kiss. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But Jesus said, \u201CJudas, would you betray the Son of Man with
        a kiss?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When the other disciples saw what was about to happen, they exclaimed,
        \u201CLord, should we fight? We brought the swords!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And one of them struck at the high priest\u2019s slave, slashing
        off his right ear.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But Jesus said, \u201CNo more of this.\u201D And he touched the man\u2019s
        ear and healed him.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Jesus spoke to the leading priests, the captains of the Temple
        guard, and the elders who had come for him. \u201CAm I some dangerous revolutionary,\u201D
        he asked, \u201Cthat you come with swords and clubs to arrest me?  "
      comments: []
    - title: Peter Denies Jesus
      content: "Why didn\u2019t you arrest me in the Temple? I was there every day.
        But this is your moment, the time when the power of darkness reigns.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So they arrested him and led him to the high priest\u2019s home.
        And Peter followed at a distance. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The guards lit a fire in the middle of the courtyard and sat around
        it, and Peter joined them there. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A servant girl noticed him in the firelight and began staring at
        him. Finally she said, \u201CThis man was one of Jesus\u2019 followers!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But Peter denied it. \u201CWoman,\u201D he said, \u201CI don\u2019t
        even know him!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "After a while someone else looked at him and said, \u201CYou must
        be one of them!\u201D\u201CNo, man, I\u2019m not!\u201D Peter retorted.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "About an hour later someone else insisted, \u201CThis must be one
        of them, because he is a Galilean, too.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But Peter said, \u201CMan, I don\u2019t know what you are talking
        about.\u201D And immediately, while he was still speaking, the rooster crowed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "At that moment the Lord turned and looked at Peter. Suddenly, the
        Lord\u2019s words flashed through Peter\u2019s mind: \u201CBefore the rooster
        crows tomorrow morning, you will deny three times that you even know me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And Peter left the courtyard, weeping bitterly.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The guards in charge of Jesus began mocking and beating him. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They blindfolded him and said, \u201CProphesy to us! Who hit you
        that time?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: Jesus before the Council
      content: 'And they hurled all sorts of terrible insults at him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'At daybreak all the elders of the people assembled, including the
        leading priests and the teachers of religious law. Jesus was led before this
        high council,[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '22:66 '
        content: Greek <b>before their Sanhedrin.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "and they said, \u201CTell us, are you the Messiah?\u201DBut he replied,
        \u201CIf I tell you, you won\u2019t believe me.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And if I ask you a question, you won\u2019t answer.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But from now on the Son of Man will be seated in the place of power
        at God\u2019s right hand.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '22:69 '
        content: See Ps 110:1.
    - title: 
      content: "They all shouted, \u201CSo, are you claiming to be the Son of God?\u201DAnd
        he replied, \u201CYou say that I am.\u201D  "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Jesus\u2019 Trial before Pilate"
      content: '  Then the entire council took Jesus to Pilate, the Roman governor. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They began to state their case: \u201CThis man has been leading our
        people astray by telling them not to pay their taxes to the Roman government
        and by claiming he is the Messiah, a king.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So Pilate asked him, \u201CAre you the king of the Jews?\u201DJesus
        replied, \u201CYou have said it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Pilate turned to the leading priests and to the crowd and said, \u201CI
        find nothing wrong with this man!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then they became insistent. \u201CBut he is causing riots by his
        teaching wherever he goes\u2014all over Judea, from Galilee to Jerusalem!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201COh, is he a Galilean?\u201D Pilate asked. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When they said that he was, Pilate sent him to Herod Antipas, because
        Galilee was under Herod\u2019s jurisdiction, and Herod happened to be in
        Jerusalem at the time.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Herod was delighted at the opportunity to see Jesus, because he had
        heard about him and had been hoping for a long time to see him perform a
        miracle. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He asked Jesus question after question, but Jesus refused to answer. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Meanwhile, the leading priests and the teachers of religious law
        stood there shouting their accusations. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then Herod and his soldiers began mocking and ridiculing Jesus. Finally,
        they put a royal robe on him and sent him back to Pilate. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: '(Herod and Pilate, who had been enemies before, became friends that
        day.)  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then Pilate called together the leading priests and other religious
        leaders, along with the people, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "and he announced his verdict. \u201CYou brought this man to me, accusing
        him of leading a revolt. I have examined him thoroughly on this point in
        your presence and find him innocent. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Herod came to the same conclusion and sent him back to us. Nothing
        this man has done calls for the death penalty. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So I will have him flogged, and then I will release him.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '23:16 '
        content: Some manuscripts add verse 17, <b>Now it was necessary for him to
          release one prisoner to them during the Passover celebration. </b>Compare
          Matt 27:15; Mark 15:6; John 18:39.
    - title: 
      content: "Then a mighty roar rose from the crowd, and with one voice they shouted,
        \u201CKill him, and release Barabbas to us!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: '(Barabbas was in prison for taking part in an insurrection in Jerusalem
        against the government, and for murder.) '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Pilate argued with them, because he wanted to release Jesus. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But they kept shouting, \u201CCrucify him! Crucify him!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the third time he demanded, \u201CWhy? What crime has he committed?
        I have found no reason to sentence him to death. So I will have him flogged,
        and then I will release him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But the mob shouted louder and louder, demanding that Jesus be crucified,
        and their voices prevailed. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So Pilate sentenced Jesus to die as they demanded. '
      comments: []
    - title: The Crucifixion
      content: 'As they had requested, he released Barabbas, the man in prison for
        insurrection and murder. But he turned Jesus over to them to do as they wished.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As they led Jesus away, a man named Simon, who was from Cyrene,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        happened to be coming in from the countryside. The soldiers seized him and
        put the cross on him and made him carry it behind Jesus. '
      comments:
      - number: '23:26 '
        content: <b>Cyrene </b>was a city in northern Africa.
    - title: 
      content: 'A large crowd trailed behind, including many grief-stricken women. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But Jesus turned and said to them, \u201CDaughters of Jerusalem,
        don\u2019t weep for me, but weep for yourselves and for your children.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the days are coming when they will say, \u2018Fortunate indeed
        are the women who are childless, the wombs that have not borne a child and
        the breasts that have never nursed.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "People will beg the mountains, \u2018Fall on us,\u2019 and plead
        with the hills, \u2018Bury us.\u2019[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '23:30 '
        content: Hos 10:8.
    - title: 
      content: "For if these things are done when the tree is green, what will happen
        when it is dry?[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '23:31 '
        content: Or <b>If these things are done to me, the living tree, what will
          happen to you, the dry tree?</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Two others, both criminals, were led out to be executed with him. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When they came to a place called The Skull,[[COMMENT(0)]] they nailed
        him to the cross. And the criminals were also crucified\u2014one on his right
        and one on his left.  "
      comments:
      - number: '23:33 '
        content: "Sometimes rendered <b>Calvary, </b>which comes from the Latin word
          for \u201Cskull.\u201D"
    - title: 
      content: "Jesus said, \u201CFather, forgive them, for they don\u2019t know
        what they are doing.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]] And the soldiers gambled for his
        clothes by throwing dice.[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '23:34a '
        content: This sentence is not included in many ancient manuscripts.
      - number: '23:34b '
        content: Greek <b>by casting lots. </b>See Ps 22:18.
    - title: 
      content: "The crowd watched and the leaders scoffed. \u201CHe saved others,\u201D
        they said, \u201Clet him save himself if he is really God\u2019s Messiah,
        the Chosen One.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The soldiers mocked him, too, by offering him a drink of sour wine. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They called out to him, \u201CIf you are the King of the Jews, save
        yourself!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "A sign was fastened above him with these words: \u201CThis is the
        King of the Jews.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "One of the criminals hanging beside him scoffed, \u201CSo you\u2019re
        the Messiah, are you? Prove it by saving yourself\u2014and us, too, while
        you\u2019re at it!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But the other criminal protested, \u201CDon\u2019t you fear God even
        when you have been sentenced to die? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "We deserve to die for our crimes, but this man hasn\u2019t done anything
        wrong.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then he said, \u201CJesus, remember me when you come into your Kingdom.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: The Death of Jesus
      content: "And Jesus replied, \u201CI assure you, today you will be with me
        in paradise.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "By this time it was about noon, and darkness fell across the whole
        land until three o\u2019clock. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The light from the sun was gone. And suddenly, the curtain in the
        sanctuary of the Temple was torn down the middle. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Jesus shouted, \u201CFather, I entrust my spirit into your hands!\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]
        And with those words he breathed his last.  "
      comments:
      - number: '23:46 '
        content: Ps 31:5.
    - title: 
      content: "When the Roman officer[[COMMENT(0)]] overseeing the execution saw
        what had happened, he worshiped God and said, \u201CSurely this man was innocent.[[COMMENT(1)]]\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '23:47a '
        content: Greek <b>the centurion.</b>
      - number: '23:47b '
        content: Or <b>righteous.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'And when all the crowd that came to see the crucifixion saw what
        had happened, they went home in deep sorrow.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '23:48 '
        content: Greek <b>went home beating their breasts.</b>
    - title: The Burial of Jesus
      content: "But Jesus\u2019 friends, including the women who had followed him
        from Galilee, stood at a distance watching.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Now there was a good and righteous man named Joseph. He was a member
        of the Jewish high council, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'but he had not agreed with the decision and actions of the other
        religious leaders. He was from the town of Arimathea in Judea, and he was
        waiting for the Kingdom of God to come. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He went to Pilate and asked for Jesus\u2019 body. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then he took the body down from the cross and wrapped it in a long
        sheet of linen cloth and laid it in a new tomb that had been carved out of
        rock. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This was done late on Friday afternoon, the day of preparation,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        as the Sabbath was about to begin.  '
      comments:
      - number: '23:54 '
        content: Greek <b>It was the day of preparation.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'As his body was taken away, the women from Galilee followed and saw
        the tomb where his body was placed. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Resurrection
      content: '  But very early on Sunday morning[[COMMENT(0)]] the women went to
        the tomb, taking the spices they had prepared. '
      comments:
      - number: '24:1 '
        content: Greek <b>But on the first day of the week, very early in the morning.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'They found that the stone had been rolled away from the entrance. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So they went in, but they didn\u2019t find the body of the Lord Jesus. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As they stood there puzzled, two men suddenly appeared to them, clothed
        in dazzling robes.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The women were terrified and bowed with their faces to the ground.
        Then the men asked, \u201CWhy are you looking among the dead for someone
        who is alive? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He isn\u2019t here! He is risen from the dead! Remember what he told
        you back in Galilee, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "that the Son of Man[[COMMENT(0)]] must be betrayed into the hands
        of sinful men and be crucified, and that he would rise again on the third
        day.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '24:7 '
        content: "\u201CSon of Man\u201D is a title Jesus used for himself."
    - title: 
      content: 'Then they remembered that he had said this. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So they rushed back from the tomb to tell his eleven disciples\u2014and
        everyone else\u2014what had happened. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It was Mary Magdalene, Joanna, Mary the mother of James, and several
        other women who told the apostles what had happened. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But the story sounded like nonsense to the men, so they didn\u2019t
        believe it. "
      comments: []
    - title: The Walk to Emmaus
      content: 'However, Peter jumped up and ran to the tomb to look. Stooping, he
        peered in and saw the empty linen wrappings; then he went home again, wondering
        what had happened.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "That same day two of Jesus\u2019 followers were walking to the village
        of Emmaus, seven miles[[COMMENT(0)]] from Jerusalem. "
      comments:
      - number: '24:13 '
        content: Greek <b>60 stadia </b>[11.1 kilometers].
    - title: 
      content: 'As they walked along they were talking about everything that had
        happened. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As they talked and discussed these things, Jesus himself suddenly
        came and began walking with them. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But God kept them from recognizing him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He asked them, \u201CWhat are you discussing so intently as you walk
        along?\u201DThey stopped short, sadness written across their faces. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then one of them, Cleopas, replied, \u201CYou must be the only person
        in Jerusalem who hasn\u2019t heard about all the things that have happened
        there the last few days.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CWhat things?\u201D Jesus asked.\u201CThe things that happened
        to Jesus, the man from Nazareth,\u201D they said. \u201CHe was a prophet
        who did powerful miracles, and he was a mighty teacher in the eyes of God
        and all the people. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But our leading priests and other religious leaders handed him over
        to be condemned to death, and they crucified him. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We had hoped he was the Messiah who had come to rescue Israel. This
        all happened three days ago.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThen some women from our group of his followers were at his
        tomb early this morning, and they came back with an amazing report. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They said his body was missing, and they had seen angels who told
        them Jesus is alive! '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Some of our men ran out to see, and sure enough, his body was gone,
        just as the women had said.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then Jesus said to them, \u201CYou foolish people! You find it so
        hard to believe all that the prophets wrote in the Scriptures.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Wasn\u2019t it clearly predicted that the Messiah would have to suffer
        all these things before entering his glory?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then Jesus took them through the writings of Moses and all the prophets,
        explaining from all the Scriptures the things concerning himself.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'By this time they were nearing Emmaus and the end of their journey.
        Jesus acted as if he were going on, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "but they begged him, \u201CStay the night with us, since it is getting
        late.\u201D So he went home with them. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As they sat down to eat,[[COMMENT(0)]] he took the bread and blessed
        it. Then he broke it and gave it to them. '
      comments:
      - number: '24:30 '
        content: Or <b>As they reclined.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Suddenly, their eyes were opened, and they recognized him. And at
        that moment he disappeared!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "They said to each other, \u201CDidn\u2019t our hearts burn within
        us as he talked with us on the road and explained the Scriptures to us?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And within the hour they were on their way back to Jerusalem. There
        they found the eleven disciples and the others who had gathered with them, '
      comments: []
    - title: Jesus Appears to the Disciples
      content: "who said, \u201CThe Lord has really risen! He appeared to Peter.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '24:34 '
        content: Greek <b>Simon.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the two from Emmaus told their story of how Jesus had appeared
        to them as they were walking along the road, and how they had recognized
        him as he was breaking the bread. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And just as they were telling about it, Jesus himself was suddenly
        standing there among them. \u201CPeace be with you,\u201D he said. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But the whole group was startled and frightened, thinking they were
        seeing a ghost!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "  \u201CWhy are you frightened?\u201D he asked. \u201CWhy are your
        hearts filled with doubt?  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Look at my hands. Look at my feet. You can see that it\u2019s really
        me. Touch me and make sure that I am not a ghost, because ghosts don\u2019t
        have bodies, as you see that I do.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As he spoke, he showed them his hands and his feet.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Still they stood there in disbelief, filled with joy and wonder.
        Then he asked them, \u201CDo you have anything here to eat?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They gave him a piece of broiled fish, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and he ate it as they watched.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then he said, \u201CWhen I was with you before, I told you that everything
        written about me in the law of Moses and the prophets and in the Psalms must
        be fulfilled.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then he opened their minds to understand the Scriptures. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And he said, \u201CYes, it was written long ago that the Messiah
        would suffer and die and rise from the dead on the third day.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "It was also written that this message would be proclaimed in the
        authority of his name to all the nations,[[COMMENT(0)]]  beginning in Jerusalem:
        \u2018There is forgiveness of sins for all who repent.\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '24:47 '
        content: Or <b>all peoples.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'You are witnesses of all these things.  '
      comments: []
    - title: The Ascension
      content: "  \u201CAnd now I will send the Holy Spirit, just as my Father promised.
        But stay here in the city until the Holy Spirit comes and fills you with
        power from heaven.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then Jesus led them to Bethany, and lifting his hands to heaven,
        he blessed them. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'While he was blessing them, he left them and was taken up to heaven. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So they worshiped him and then returned to Jerusalem filled with
        great joy. '
      comments: []
